{"type":"message","id":"23356ec6","parentId":"2343a546","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:28.811Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_931a04tap7hn_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"NVDA NVIDIA Q1 2026 earnings revenue earnings per share\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2023,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54119c73b16c75c9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNVIDIA (NVDA) Earnings Report Q1 2026 | Beat, EPS & Revenue | 24/7 Wall St.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54119c73b16c75c9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://247wallst.com/companies/nvda/earnings/2026/Q1\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8505596a66e045c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# NVDA Q1 2026 Q4 2026 Q3 2026 Q2 2026 Q1 2026 Earnings. NVDA +39.0% vs S&P +22.7%. NVIDIA delivered a powerful beat to open fiscal 2026, posting first-quarter earnings of $0.81 per share against a $0.75 consensus estimate, an 8.00% beat, even as a $4.50 billion charge tied to H20 inventory and purchase obligations weighed heavily o… Read more NVIDIA delivered a powerful beat to open fiscal 2026, posting first-quarter earnings of $0.81 per share against a $0.75 consensus estimate, an 8.00% beat, even as a $4.50 billion charge tied to H20 inventory and purchase obligations weighed heavily on results after the U.S. Government imposed new export licensing requirements for H20 products into China in April. Revenue climbed 69.2% year-over-year to $44.06 billion, anchored by a dominant Data Center segment that contributed $39.11 billion, with networking revenue alone surging 64% sequentially as Blackwell-based NVLink and Ethernet AI solutions gained rapid adoption. Q1 2026 vs Q1 2025, source: SEC Filings.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8505596a66e045c\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.95857275\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"12d3f11e5037187d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNVIDIA EPS - Earnings per Share 2012-2026 | NVDA | MacroTrends\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"12d3f11e5037187d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.macrotrends.net/stocks/charts/NVDA/nvidia/eps-earnings-per-share-diluted\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a91904762d35fe5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## NVIDIA EPS - Earnings per Share 2012-2026 | NVDA. NVIDIA annual and quarterly earnings per share history from 2012 to 2026. Earnings per share can be defined as a company's net earnings or losses attributable to common shareholders per diluted share base, which includes all convertible securities and debt, options and warrants. * NVIDIA EPS for the quarter ending January 31, 2026 was **$1.76**, a **97.75% increase** year-over-year. * NVIDIA EPS for the twelve months ending January 31, 2026 was **$4.90**, a **66.67% increase** year-over-year. * NVIDIA 2026 annual EPS was **$4.9**, a **66.67% increase** from 2025. The company's GPU platforms are playing a major role in developing multi-billion-dollar end-markets like robotics and self-driving vehicles.NVIDIA is a dominant name in the Data Center, professional visualization and gaming markets where Intel and Advanced Micro Devices are playing a catch-up role. | Intel (INTC) | United States | $311.588B | 0.00 |. | SUMCO (SUOPY) | Japan | $4.406B | 0.00 |. | Amtech Systems (ASYS) | United States | $0.213B | 0.00 |.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a91904762d35fe5\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9372167\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7702a1740de476c2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNVIDIA First Quarter 2026 Earnings: Revenues Beat Expectations, EPS Lags\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTEN