{"type":"message","id":"02783394","parentId":"23356ec6","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:28.812Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_931a04tap7hn_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"AMD Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1828,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"33e8e7fce023f386\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD Q1 2026 earnings: revenue up 38% on AI chip demand\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"33e8e7fce023f386\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://x.com/qz/status/2051777008808738990\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0010709c8d6f4963\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD revenue climbs 38% as data center and AI chip demand powers first quarter: The chipmaker's data center segment brought in $5.8 billion,\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0010709c8d6f4963\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999926\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2b30395093dd933a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD Q1 Earnings Beat Estimates, Revenues Rise on Data Center ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2b30395093dd933a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2916220/amd-q1-earnings-beat-estimates-revenues-rise-on-data-center-demand\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c488b1a28a9e85d7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWe use cookies to understand how you use our site and to improve your experience. By pressing \\\"Accept All\\\" or closing out of this banner, you consent to the use of all cookies and similar technologies and the sharing of information they collect with third parties. In addition, whether you \\\"Accept All,\\\" Deny Optional,\\\" click the X or otherwise continue to use the site, you accept our Privacy Policy and Terms of Service, revised from time to time. Based on page view growth over the last 3 trading days. Revenues climbed 37.8% year over year to $10.25 billion and beat the Zacks Consensus Estimate by 5.3%. Year-over-year growth is expected to be driven by strong growth in the Data Center segment, growth in the Client and Gaming segment and a double-digit growth in the Embedded segment.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c488b1a28a9e85d7\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99999213\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8ee132ec0d6875a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD posts Q1 2026 data center revenue of $5.8bn, forecasts $120bn server CPU income by 2030 - DCD\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8ee132ec0d6875a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.datacenterdynamics.com/en/news/amd-posts-q1-2026-data-center-revenue-of-58bn-forecasts-120bn-server-cpu-income-by-2030/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf71bded78379902\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe growth was primarily driven by strong demand for the company’s Epyc CPUs and Instinct GPUs as AI compute needs continue to ramp up, the company said. Speaking to analysts on the company’s earnings call, AMD CEO Lisa Su said the results marked “a clear inflection in our growth trajectory and a structural shift in our business,” with AMD’s data center segment now the primary driver of revenue and earnings growth. “As a result, we now expect server CPU revenue to grow by more than 70 percent YoY in the second quarter, with robust growth continuing through the second half of 2026 and into 2027 as we ramp our next-generation Epyc processors.”. In reference to the company’s October 2025 deal with OpenAI to also deploy 6GW-worth of GPUs starting the second half of 2026, Su said it was “going really well.” OpenAI had previously said it would build a 1GW data center using AMD MI450 chips, but no information about where OpenAI, or Meta, will be deploying the initial GPUs has been provided.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf71bded78379902\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999877\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"92d901381c90b585\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD Earnings: AI Data Center Explosion! | Q1 2026 Results Analysis\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"92d901381c90b585\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JcIrvyQHg3Q\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b0987956e4e17cf4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD (NASDAQ: AMD) just dropped its Q1 2026 earnings, and the numbers are massive. Led by CEO Dr. Lisa Su, the chipmaker crushed expectations\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b0987956e4e17cf4\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999871\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"117faa9ec4d17363\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD Earnings: AI-Driven Data Center Growth Signals New Era Dominance | Trefis\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"117faa9ec4d17363\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.trefis.com/stock/amd/articles2/598792/amd-earnings-ai-driven-data-center-growth-signals-new-era-dominance/2026-05-08\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0da2ce43ce3aef3c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAMD: Advanced Micro Devices logo. Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) reported its 2026 Q1 earnings on 5/5/2026 after market close. The earnings report confirms a significant shift in AMD’s business, with the data center now firmly established as the main growth engine. This is driven by the irreversible trend of AI adoption and the increasing demand for high-performance computing. To better understand how the market might digest these fundamentals, it helps to examine how AMD stock has historically reacted to earnings. The Data Center segment was the primary growth driver, with revenue surging 57% year-over-year to $5.8 billion. Wall Street reacted positively to the strong results and guidance, with analysts highlighting the impressive growth in the Data Center segment. How Will Palantir Technologies Stock React To Its Upcoming Earnings? How Will Loews Stock React To Its Upcoming Earnings? How Will BWX Technologies Stock React To Its Upcoming Earnings? How Will Fabrinet Stock React To Its Upcoming Earnings?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0da2ce43ce3aef3c\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99997723\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"AMD Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1828,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"33e8e7fce023f386\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAMD Q1 2026 earnings: revenue up 38% on AI chip demand\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"33e8e7fce023f386\">>>","url":"https://x.com/qz/status/2051777008808738990","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0010709c8d6f4963\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAMD revenue climbs 38% as data center and AI chip demand powers first quarter: The chipmaker's data center segment brought in $5.8 billion,\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0010709c8d6f4963\">>>","score":0.9999926},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2b30395093dd933a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAMD Q1 Earnings Beat Estimates, Revenues Rise on Data Center ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2b30395093dd933a\">>>","url":"https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2916220/amd-q1-earnings-beat-estimates-revenues-rise-on-data-center-demand","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c488b1a28a9e85d7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWe use cookies to understand how you use our site and to improve your experience. By pressing \"Accept All\" or closing out of this banner, you consent to 