ital logo displayed on a tablet screen in front of a data center server room. Want to stay updated on the latest earnings announcements and upcoming reports for companies like Constellation Energy? Sign up for **Earnings360's daily newsletter** to receive timely earnings updates on Constellation Energy and other key companies, straight to your email. ## About Constellation Energy. Constellation Energy (NASDAQ:CEG) (NASDAQ:CEG) is a U.S.-focused energy company that owns and operates a diverse portfolio of power-generation assets and provides energy products and services to wholesale and retail customers. Its principal activities include operating a fleet of baseload and flexible generation — notably including nuclear power plants — developing and managing renewable energy resources such as wind and solar, and supplying electricity and related energy solutions to commercial, industrial and wholesale markets. Sign up for MarketBeat All Access to gain access to MarketBeat's full suite of research tools.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cf196d82016b19aa\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8657814\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Constellation Energy CEG Q1 2026 earnings revenue","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1908,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"798522542edfbd80\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nConstellation Energy Q1 2026 earnings preview - MSN\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"798522542edfbd80\">>>","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/topstocks/constellation-energy-q1-2026-earnings-preview/ar-AA22IanC","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abb9fe23df360003\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe consensus EPS Estimate is $2.61 (+22.0% Y/Y) and the consensus Revenue Estimate is $8.71B (+30.2% Y/Y). Over the last 2 years, CEG has beaten EPS estimates\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abb9fe23df360003\">>>","score":0.96323407},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4502996144b647a0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nConstellation Energy (CEG) Earnings Date & Report - Investing.com\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4502996144b647a0\">>>","url":"https://www.investing.com/equities/constellation-energy-earnings","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b6d98899c9223b67\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nConstellation Energy (CEG) Earnings Dates & Reports ; Latest Release. Feb 23, 2026 ; EPS / Forecast. 2.30 / 2.31 ; Revenue / Forecast. 6.07B / 4.95B ; EPS Revisions.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b6d98899c9223b67\">>>","score":0.94276565},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67e140f5721cdf40\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nConstellation Energy Stock is Down 13% in 2026: What the Q1 2026 Earnings Must Show  | TIKR.com\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67e140f5721cdf40\">>>","url":"https://www.tikr.com/blog/constellation-energy-stock-is-down-13-in-2026-what-the-q1-2026-earnings-must-show","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0895b3f26c084dad\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Constellation Energy Stock is Down 13% in 2026: What the Q1 2026 Earnings Must Show. The Calpine acquisition fundamentally repriced what Constellation Energy stock is worth on a forward earnings basis, and the Street’s reaction to the March guidance call has not closed that gap yet. EBITDA tells the sharper story here: consensus estimates show CEG’s EBITDA surging from $0.84 billion in Q4 2025 to $2.02 billion in Q1 2026, a 189% year-over-year increase driven directly by Calpine adding its natural gas and geothermal earnings to the combined platform. The catalyst is the Q1 2026 earnings call on May 11: the number to watch is whether Q1 EBITDA tracks toward consensus at $2.02 billion, confirming that the Calpine integration is delivering at the pace the model requires. ***With 20 of 21 analysts bullish on Constellation Energy stock and the May 11 earnings call days away, the window to build a position ahead of a potential catalyst is short: access real-time analyst estimates and price target data on CEG with TIKR for free →***.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0895b3f26c084dad\">>>","score":0.9126935},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ea3dfd083cd0f8b4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nConstellation Energy Earnings Estimates, EPS & Revenue | NASDAQ:CEG | Benzinga\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ea3dfd083cd0f8b4\">>>","url":"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/CEG/earnings","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e4da5bb1fa1e9f1b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBrowse[earnings estimates, EPS, and revenue](https://www.benzinga.com/calendars/earnings) on all stocks. * [Pre-market Stock Analysis and News](https://www.benzinga.com/premarket). | CEG | Constellation Energy | Q4 | $2.44 | $2.23 | $2.30 | 3.14% | $5.38B | $5.56B | $6.07B | 9.30% | 02/24/2026 | [Get Alert](https://www.benzinga.com/profile/portfolio/?action=login&utm_source=calendars) |. | CEG | Constellation Energy | Q3 | $2.74 | $3.09 | $3.04 | -1.62% | $6.55B | $6.38B | $6.57B | 2.97% | 11/07/2025 | [Get Alert](https://www.benzinga.com/profile/portfolio/?action=login&utm_source=calendars) |. | CEG | Constellation Energy | Q2 | $1.68 | $1.83 | $1.91 | 4.37% | $5.47B | $4.95B | $6.10B | 23.24% | 08/07/2025 | [Get Alert](https://www.benzinga.com/profile/portfolio/?action=login&utm_source=calendars) |. | CEG | Constellation Energy | Q1 | $1.82 | $2.15 | $2.14 | -0.47% | $6.16B | $5.44B | $6.79B | 24.78% | 05/06/2025 | [Get Alert](https://www.benzinga.com/profile/portfolio/?action=login&utm_source=calendars) |. | CEG | Constellation Energy | Q4 | -$0.11 | $1.86 | $2.44 | 31.18% | $5.80B | $3.46B | $5.38B | 55.55% | 02/18/2025 | [Get Alert](https://www.benzinga.com/profile/portfolio/?action=login&utm_source=calendars) |.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e4da5bb1fa1e9f1b\">>>","score":0.87981987},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2224ff0cdf8cb169\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCEG Q1 2026 Earnings Report on 5/11/2026\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2224ff0cdf8cb169\">>>","url":"https://www.marketbeat.com/earnings/reports/2026-5-11-745964-stock/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cf196d82016b19aa\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDigitalOcean logo displayed on server racks inside a data center facility. Western Digital logo displayed on a tablet screen in front of a data center server room. Want to stay updated on the latest earnings announcements and upcoming reports for companies like Constellation Energy? Sign up for **Earnings360's daily newsletter** to receive timely earnings updates on Constellation Energy and other key companies, straight to your email. ## About Constellation Energy. Constellation Energy (NASDAQ:CEG) (NASDAQ:CEG) is a U.S.-focused energy company that owns and operates a diverse portfolio of power-generation assets and provides energy products and services to wholesale and retail customers. Its principal activities include operating a fleet of baseload and flexible generation — notably including nuclear power plants — developing and managing renewable energy resources such as wind and solar, and supplying electricity and related energy solutions to commercial, industrial and wholesale markets. Sign up for MarketBeat All Access to gain access to MarketBeat's full suite of research tools.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cf196d82016b19aa\">>>","score":0.8657814}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387548812}}
{"type":"message","id":"4bcaa7d0","parentId":"874365d4","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:28.814Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_931a04tap7hn_5","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Broadcom AVGO Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1836,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"70a5d215827dd747\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom (AVGO) Q1 2026 Revenue Reaches $19.3 Billion; AI Chip Growth Projected to Exceed $100 Billion by 2027 | KuCoin\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"70a5d215827dd747\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.kucoin.com/news/flash/broadcom-avgo-q1-2026-revenue-hits-19-3-billion-ai-chip-growth-expected-to-surpass-100-billion-by-2027\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1383bacbeb2dcda\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Broadcom (AVGO) Q1 2026 Revenue Reaches $19.3 Billion; AI Chip Growth Projected to Exceed $100 Billion by 2027. Broadcom (AVGO) reported Q1 2026 revenue of $19.3 billion, a 29% year-over-year increase, with net income rising 34% to $7.3 billion. The company secured new AI chip agreements with Alphabet (GOOGL) and Anthropic. CEO Hock Tan anticipates AI chip revenue to exceed $100 billion by 2027. Analysts project AVGO’s earnings per share to grow 66% in 2026 and 57% in 2027. As competition in the AI sector intensifies and AVGO’s stock price declined this week, could Broadcom’s stock become a buy for the remainder of 2026? The company’s first-quarter earnings for fiscal year 2026 were outstanding, with revenue reaching $19.3 billion for the quarter ended February 1, a 29% increase year-over-year. Its earnings per share are projected to increase by 66% in fiscal year 2026 and by 57% in fiscal year 2027. Additionally, CEO Hock Tan stated that revenue from the company’s AI chips will exceed $100 billion by 2027.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f1383bacbeb2dcda\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999877\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5c14ab73bba63f7f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom (AVGO) Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript - Fortune\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5c14ab73bba63f7f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://fortune.com/company/broadcom/earnings/q1-2026/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8725abcfed454702\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* **Hock Tan** - President and CEO, Broadcom Inc. **Operator**Welcome to Broadcom Inc.'s first quarter fiscal year 2026 financial results conference call. At this time, for opening remarks and introductions, I would like to turn the call over to Ji Yoo, Head of Investor Relations of Broadcom Inc. This conference call is being webcast live, and an audio replay of the call can be accessed for one year through the investors section of Broadcom's website. During the prepared comments, Hock and Kirsten will be providing details of our first quarter fiscal year 2026 results, guidance for our second quarter of fiscal year 2026, as well as commentary regarding the business environment. In our fiscal Q1 2026, total revenue reached a record $19.3 billion, and that's up 29% year-on-year and exceeding our guidance on the back of better than expected growth in AI semiconductors. Driving this is AI revenue growth, which will accelerate very sharply to 140% year-on-year to $10.7 billion.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8725abcfed454702\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999814\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f559433b49985edd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom Q1 seen up 29% YOY as AI revenue nears $8 billion ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f559433b49985edd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.spglobal.com/market-intelligence/en/news-insights/research/2026/02/broadcom-q1-seen-up-29percent-yoy-as-ai-revenue-nears-usd8-billion-margins-set-to-ease\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cdcc5332ffbdd55b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom Q1 seen up 29% YOY as AI revenue nears $8 billion, margins set to ease · Discover insights with the Visible Alpha Estimates dataset.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cdcc5332ffbdd55b\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99996376\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc123cdefb9c5542\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom Q1 FY 2026 Earnings Driven by XPU Momentum - Futurum\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc123cdefb9c5542\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://futurumgroup.com/insights/broadcom-q1-fy-2026-earnings-driven-by-xpu-momentum/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8b33c04c4545d75f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGet organization-wide instant access to market sizing and decision-maker data in a self-serve subscription model with analyst support. Turn your message into motion with analyst-hosted video, live events, digital media, and content strategies. # Futurum Research 2026: Key Issues and Predictions. Broadcom’s quarter was shaped by rapid expansion in AI semiconductor revenue and a higher Q2 FY 2026 revenue outlook. **Analyst Take:** Broadcom’s Q1 FY 2026 narrative is increasingly anchored in custom AI XPUs and the networking silicon required to scale AI clusters. The company also positioned AI networking as a growing portion of AI revenue, with roadmap claims tied to Tomahawk switching and SerDes transitions. Broadcom emphasized that AI networking is becoming a larger share of its AI semiconductor revenue, with Q1 FY 2026 positioned as a step-up quarter and Q2 FY 2026 framed as a further mix increase. ***Disclosure: Futurum is a research and advisory firm that engages or has engaged in research, analysis, and advisory services with many technology companies, including those mentioned in this article.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8b33c04c4545d75f\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99996173\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a008664365aef592\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMLQ.ai | AI for investors\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a008664365aef592\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mlq.ai/earnings/highlight/AVGO-broadcom-targets-191-billion-in-revenu-798e6b/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07b390d55da398d6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Broadcom targets $19.1 billion in revenue for Q1 2026. Within this, we expect Q1 AI semiconductor revenue of $8.2 billion, up approximately 100% year on year.\\\". Broadcom Inc. aims for a remarkable revenue rise in Q1 2026, driven significantly by AI semiconductor sales with an expected growth of 100% year over year. Let me now provide additional detail on our Q4 financial performance.\\\\n\\\\nConsolidated revenue was a record $18 billion for the quarter, up 28% from a year ago. Revenue for our Semiconductor Solutions segment was a record $11.1 billion with growth accelerating to 35% year on year driven by AI.\\\\n\\\\nSemiconductor revenue represented 61% of total revenue in the quarter. Now moving to infrastructure software.\\\\n\\\\nRevenue for Infrastructure Software of $6.9 billion was up 19% year on year and represented 39% of total revenue. We forecast semiconductor revenue of approximately $12.3 billion, up 50% year on year.\\\\n\\\\nWithin this, we expect Q1 AI semiconductor revenue of $8.2 billion, up approximately 100% year on year.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07b390d55da398d6\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99992216\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Broadcom AVGO Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1836,"exte