026/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8725abcfed454702\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n* **Hock Tan** - President and CEO, Broadcom Inc. **Operator**Welcome to Broadcom Inc.'s first quarter fiscal year 2026 financial results conference call. At this time, for opening remarks and introductions, I would like to turn the call over to Ji Yoo, Head of Investor Relations of Broadcom Inc. This conference call is being webcast live, and an audio replay of the call can be accessed for one year through the investors section of Broadcom's website. During the prepared comments, Hock and Kirsten will be providing details of our first quarter fiscal year 2026 results, guidance for our second quarter of fiscal year 2026, as well as commentary regarding the business environment. In our fiscal Q1 2026, total revenue reached a record $19.3 billion, and that's up 29% year-on-year and exceeding our guidance on the back of better than expected growth in AI semiconductors. Driving this is AI revenue growth, which will accelerate very sharply to 140% year-on-year to $10.7 billion.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8725abcfed454702\">>>","score":0.9999814},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f559433b49985edd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBroadcom Q1 seen up 29% YOY as AI revenue nears $8 billion ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f559433b49985edd\">>>","url":"https://www.spglobal.com/market-intelligence/en/news-insights/research/2026/02/broadcom-q1-seen-up-29percent-yoy-as-ai-revenue-nears-usd8-billion-margins-set-to-ease","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cdcc5332ffbdd55b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBroadcom Q1 seen up 29% YOY as AI revenue nears $8 billion, margins set to ease · Discover insights with the Visible Alpha Estimates dataset.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cdcc5332ffbdd55b\">>>","score":0.99996376},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc123cdefb9c5542\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBroadcom Q1 FY 2026 Earnings Driven by XPU Momentum - Futurum\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc123cdefb9c5542\">>>","url":"https://futurumgroup.com/insights/broadcom-q1-fy-2026-earnings-driven-by-xpu-momentum/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8b33c04c4545d75f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGet organization-wide instant access to market sizing and decision-maker data in a self-serve subscription model with analyst support. Turn your message into motion with analyst-hosted video, live events, digital media, and content strategies. # Futurum Research 2026: Key Issues and Predictions. Broadcom’s quarter was shaped by rapid expansion in AI semiconductor revenue and a higher Q2 FY 2026 revenue outlook. **Analyst Take:** Broadcom’s Q1 FY 2026 narrative is increasingly anchored in custom AI XPUs and the networking silicon required to scale AI clusters. The company also positioned AI networking as a growing portion of AI revenue, with roadmap claims tied to Tomahawk switching and SerDes transitions. Broadcom emphasized that AI networking is becoming a larger share of its AI semiconductor revenue, with Q1 FY 2026 positioned as a step-up quarter and Q2 FY 2026 framed as a further mix increase. ***Disclosure: Futurum is a research and advisory firm that engages or has engaged in research, analysis, and advisory services with many technology companies, including those mentioned in this article.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8b33c04c4545d75f\">>>","score":0.99996173},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a008664365aef592\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMLQ.ai | AI for investors\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a008664365aef592\">>>","url":"https://mlq.ai/earnings/highlight/AVGO-broadcom-targets-191-billion-in-revenu-798e6b/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"07b390d55da398d6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Broadcom targets $19.1 billion in revenue for Q1 2026. Within this, we expect Q1 AI semiconductor revenue of $8.2 billion, up approximately 100% year on year.\". Broadcom Inc. aims for a remarkable revenue rise in Q1 2026, driven significantly by AI semiconductor sales with an expected growth of 100% year over year. Let me now provide additional detail on our Q4 financial performance.\\n\\nConsolidated revenue was a record $18 billion for the quarter, up 28% from a year ago. Revenue for our Semiconductor Solutions segment was a record $11.1 billion with growth accelerating to 35% year on year driven by AI.\\n\\nSemiconductor revenue represented 61% of total revenue in the quarter. Now moving to infrastructure software.\\n\\nRevenue for Infrastructure Software of $6.9 billion was up 19% year on year and represented 39% of total revenue. We forecast semiconductor revenue of approximately $12.3 billion, up 50% year on year.\\n\\nWithin this, we expect Q1 AI semiconductor revenue of $8.2 billion, up approximately 100% year on year.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"07b390d55da398d6\">>>","score":0.99992216}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387548812}}
{"type":"message","id":"0630a4f9","parentId":"4bcaa7d0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:41.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have data on:\n1. NVDA: Q1 FY2026 - EPS $0.81 (beat $0.75 estimate), Revenue $44.06B (+69% YoY), Data Center $39.11B\n2. AMD: Q1 2026 - Revenue $10.25B (+38% YoY), Data Center $5.8B (+57% YoY)\n3. MU: Record fiscal Q2 with revenue $23.9B (Feb 2026 quarter), HBM sold out for 2026\n4. CEG: Q1 2026 earnings on May 11 - consensus EPS $2.61, revenue $8.71B, EBITDA expected $2.02B\n5. AVGO: Q1 FY2026 - Revenue $19.3B (+29% YoY), AI revenue $10.7B (+140% YoY), EPS growth 66% in 2026\n\n\nI should pull data on a few more companies to round out the coverage before organizing everything by category.","thinkingSignature":"2bd989db97fb82e92da557d4edb6814836feb7a3910c7251506ff262d6eedcd7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Microsoft MSFT Q3 2026 earnings revenue Azure AI"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Meta META Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI advertising"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_3","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Marvell MRVL Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI data center"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_4","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Arista Networks ANET Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI networking"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_5","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Eaton ETN Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center power"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13426,"output":437,"cacheRead":42336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56199,"cost":{"input":0.0040278,"output":0.0005244,"cacheRead":0.0025401599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007092359999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778387548814,"responseId":"064f3d61e937a9eea25cacde1c700d37"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd1a3a86","parentId":"0630a4f9","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:45.474Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Microsoft MSFT Q3 2026 earnings revenue Azure AI\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1580,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7a8482107bcfd0f2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMicrosoft (MSFT) Fiscal Q3 2026 Earnings Recap: Cloud Strength Fuels Beats Amid Capex Surge\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7a8482107bcfd0f2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://tickeron.com/earnings/MSFT/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"58a5dd9748a28134\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n### MSFT is expected to report earnings to $4.23 per share on July 28. Microsoft's fiscal third quarter of 2026, ended March 31, underscores the company's dominance in cloud computing and artificial intelligence amid fierce competition and massive infrastructure investments. As the world's largest software provider, Microsoft relies heavily on Azure growth and AI innovations like Copilot to drive revenue. With shares down over 10% year-to-date prior to earnings due to capex concerns, this report provides critical insight into whether accelerating AI demand justifies escalating spending, influencing not just Microsoft but the broader tech sector's valuation. Microsoft reported total revenue of $82.9 billion for the quarter ended March 31, 2026, up 18% (15% in constant currency) from $70.1 billion a year earlier, exceeding analyst expectations of around $81.4 billion. Guidance for Q4 includes revenue of $86.7-87.8 billion (13-15% growth), Azure growth of 39-40% constant currency, and capex exceeding $40 billion.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"58a5dd9748a28134\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.999972\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"78b51b8650157974\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMicrosoft (MSFT) Q3 earnings report 2026 - CNBC\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"78b51b8650157974\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/microsoft-msft-q3-earnings-report-2026.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5f51bac688216ae9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Microsoft](https://www.cnbc.com/quotes/MSFT/) reported better-than-expected quarterly results on Wednesday and told investors that capital expenditures for the year will reach $190 billion due to soaring memory costs. Microsoft's revenue grew 18% year over year in the quarter, which ended on March 31, according to a [statement](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q3/press-release-webcast). With respect to guidance, Microsoft's finance chief, Amy Hood, called for $86.7 billion to $87.8 billion in fiscal fourth-quarter revenue. Microsoft reported $31.9 billion in fiscal third-quarter capital expenditures and finance leases, up 49% and less than the $34.9 billion consensus among analysts polled by Visible Alpha. Across the tech industry, infrastructure providers are being forced to pay up for memory, which is in midst of a [global crunch](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/28/tech-hyperscalers-q1-earnings-after-iran-war-lifts-energy-ai-prices.html) due to AI demand. The number was up by $2 billion from [the prior quarter](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html). [Any cloud provider](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/openai-drift-from-microsoft-to-amazon-turns-aggressive-after-subtlety.html) can now serve OpenAI models under the new terms, following years of exclusivity for Azure. **WATCH:** [Microsoft tops revenue and earnings estimates, Azure revenue grows 40%](https://www.cnbc.com/video/2026/04/29/microsoft-tops-revenue-and-earnings-ewstimates-azure-revenue-grows-40-percent.html).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5f51bac688216ae9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999443\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4f56d8cf337f541e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMicrosoft Fiscal Year 2026 Third Quarter Earnings Conference Call\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4f56d8cf337f541e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/events/fy-2026/earnings-fy-2026-q3\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a14193655d7a68ef\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nLet me maybe start with Azure, which, given its size and its growth rates, where we’ve talked about acceleration from where we are, which is the guide at 39 to 40 into a bigger number in the second half the calendar year, when you start to see that type of growth rate on the size of the business we have, the amount of spend being done on short-term assets, which is really the thing that correlates with revenue, as opposed to the third of that number-ish, that’s going into 15-year assets, or some lumpy timing from lease contracts that can get confusing, I think in so many ways, this just reminds us of the last cycle. And so, when you think about spending that amount of capital, putting it into production, seeing some delay before it turns into revenue ready, having the book of business, I think it’s over $600 billion of revenue that we still need to deliver, and that’s before we’re starting to see the acceleration in seats that we’re seeing on Copilot, I do feel very good about, frankly, that number.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a14193655d7a68ef\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9995956\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"27807cd0240908a7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMicrosoft's $190 Billion AI Pivot | MSFT Q3 FY26 Earnings Breakdown\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"27807cd0240908a7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J4EDYfBag_E\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44a36b73c7504216\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*Top-Line Financials:* Microsoft reported a massive $82.9 billion in total revenue, up 18% year-over-year, alongside an operating income of\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44a36b73c7504216\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9995122\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef64d8b9d09d6cfa\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFY26 Q3 - Performance - Investor Relations - Microsoft\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef64d8b9d09d6cfa\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q3/performance\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1259d8d434c158a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n![Image 1](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q3/performance). [](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q3/performance). [Investor Relations](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/default). *   [Home](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/default). *   [Home](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/default). *   [Annual Reports](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/annual-reports). *   [SEC Filings](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/sec-filings). *   [Events](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/events/default). *   [Investor Information](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/investor-information). *   [Contacts](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/contact-information). *   [Press Release & Webcast](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q3/press-release-webcast). *   [Income Statements](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q3/income-statements). *   [Comprehensive Income](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earning