cid=DSM_Footer_AI). *   [Dynamics 365](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics-365). *   [Microsoft 365](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/business). *   [Small Business](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/store/b/business?icid=CNavBusinessStore). *   [Accessibility](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/accessibility). *   [Sustainability](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sustainability/). *   [Manage cookies](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q3/performance#).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1259d8d434c158a\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.996597\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["query","provider","count","tookMs","externalContent","results"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387565474}}
{"type":"message","id":"09317784","parentId":"bd1a3a86","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:45.475Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Meta META Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI advertising\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1497,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"356c5ea2ae77ab22\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Q1 2026 earnings: AI capex raised to $145B - Quartz\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"356c5ea2ae77ab22\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://qz.com/meta-q1-2026-earnings-ai-spending-capex-stock-042926\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c99227cbbe453081\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAdvertising revenue totaled $55.02 billion, up 33% year-over-year. Ad impressions rose 19% and the average price per ad increased 12% over\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c99227cbbe453081\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9594935\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"250cd96ffc6b1d49\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Q1 Earnings Preview: Can Advertising Growth Support Massive AI Investments? | Investing.com UK\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"250cd96ffc6b1d49\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://uk.investing.com/analysis/meta-q1-earnings-preview-can-advertising-growth-support-massive-ai-investments-200624257\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e5b2042a7d8a8c6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Platforms (NASDAQ:META)​ is set to report its first-quarter 2026 earnings on 29 April after the US market close, with a conference call scheduled later that evening. The update will be a key test of whether the social media giant can sustain strong advertising growth while ramping up significant investment in artificial intelligence infrastructure. The company reported Q4 revenue of around $59.9 billion and earnings per share of $8.88, beating expectations and reinforcing confidence in its core advertising business. ​Expected is Q1 revenue of $55.46 billion, up 31% compared to a year ago,  advertising revenue of $53.93 billion (up 30%), pre-tax profit of $20.32 billion (up around 10%) and earnings per share at $6.73, nearly 5% higher than in Q1 2025. ​Consensus forecasts point to Q1 earnings of roughly $6.73 per share, representing modest year-on-year growth of around 5%, alongside revenue expectations in the region of $55.46 billion, up around 31% compared to a year ago.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7e5b2042a7d8a8c6\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.95931095\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2fa6feadcc3dac37\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Q1 Revenue Soars 33% in Q1, Net Profit Hits $26.8 Billion Ahead of Mass Layoffs\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2fa6feadcc3dac37\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://variety.com/2026/digital/news/meta-q1-2026-earnings-1236733502/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"120bcc5250e00af9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTech giant raises guidance on 2026 capital spending, fueled by AI investments, to as much as $145 billion. Even as Meta continues make money hand over fist, the tech giant is set to make a large round of layoffs to optimize operations — and as it continues to plow billions into AI projects. Meta, the parent of Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp, reported revenue of $56.3 billion for the first quarter of 2026 as ad sales were strong in the period. That’s up 33% from the year-prior period. In reporting its latest quarterly results, Meta said it continues to monitor active legal and regulatory matters, including “headwinds in the EU and the U.S. that could significantly impact our business and financial results.” The company said, “For example, we continue to see scrutiny on youth-related issues and have additional trials scheduled for this year in the U.S., which may ultimately result in a material loss.”.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"120bcc5250e00af9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.94608605\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dcf1a1fe9b3f85cb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Q1 2026 earnings report - CNBC\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dcf1a1fe9b3f85cb\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/meta-q1-earnings-report-2026.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0c047f51902c1c6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe jump reflects Meta CEO [Mark Zuckerberg's](https://www.cnbc.com/mark-zuckerberg/) focus on artificial intelligence investments, which have yet to produce new revenue streams but have strengthened the company's core advertising business. Zuckerberg has spent the past three months continuing his company's deeper push into AI following a strategy shift and talent overhaul that he initiated in June with the [$14.3 billion investment in Scale AI](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/12/scale-ai-founder-wang-announces-exit-for-meta-part-of-14-billion-deal.html) and the hiring of CEO Alexandr Wang. Meta and three other hyperscalers — [Alphabet](/quotes/GOOGL/), [Amazon](/quotes/AMZN/) and [Microsoft](/quotes/MSFT/) — all reported results on Wednesday, [updating investors for](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/openai-looms-over-earnings-from-tech-hyperscalers.html) the first time since the U.S. began combat operations in Iran in late February. The company said last week that it's laying off about [10% of its workforce](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/23/meta-will-cut-10percent-of-workforce-as-it-pushes-more-into-ai.html), or 8,000 employees, while no longer hiring people for 6,000 open roles. Those cuts follow January's layoffs affecting about 1,000 people in the [company's Reality Labs unit](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/13/meta-lays-off-vr-employees-underscoring-zuckerbergs-pivot-to-ai.html), and another round in March targeting hundreds of staffers in areas like Facebook, global operations and sales. **WATCH**: [Retail investors are expecting strong Meta earnings, says Cboe's J.J. Kinahan](https://www.cnbc.com/video/2026/04/24/retail-investors-are-expecting-strong-meta-earnings-says-cboes-jj-kinahan.html).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0c047f51902c1c6\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9311691\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bdbb2dc84161e8c0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta Reports Big Revenue Jump and Projected Spending Increase\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bdbb2dc84161e8c0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.wsj.com/business/earnings/meta-meta-q1-2026-earnings-report-ae021875?eafs_enabled=false\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fac2d0224d14fb3b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSales grew 33% in the first quarter to $56.3 billion, but company raises capex outlook as component prices rise.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fac2d0224d14fb3b\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8430832\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Meta META Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI advertising","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1497,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"356c5ea2ae77ab22\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Q1 2026 earnings: AI capex raised to $145B - Quartz\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"356c5ea2ae77ab22\">>>","url":"https://qz.com/meta-q1-2026-earnings-ai-spending-capex-stock-042926","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c99227cbbe453081\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAdvertising revenue totaled $55.02 billion, up 33% year-over-year. Ad impressions rose 19% and the average price per ad increased 12% over\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c99227cbbe453081\">>>","score":0.9594935},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"250cd96ffc6b1d49\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Q1 Earnings Preview: Can Advertising Growth Support Massive AI Investments? | Investing.com UK\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"250cd96ffc6b1d49\">>>","url":"https://uk.investing.com/analysis/meta-q1-earnings-preview-can-advertising-growth-support-massive-ai-investments-200624257","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7e5b2042a7d8a8c6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Platforms (NASDAQ:META)​ is set to report its first-quarter 2026 earnings on 29 April after the US market close, with a conference call scheduled later that evening. The update will be a key test of whether the social media giant can sustain strong advertising growth while ramping up significant investment in artificial intelligence infrastructure. The company reported Q4 revenue of around $59.9 billion and earnings per share of $8.88, beating expectations and reinforcing confidence in its core advertising business. ​Expected is Q1 revenue of $55.46 billion, up 31% compared to a year ago,  advertising revenue of $53.93 billion (up 30%), pre-tax profit of $20.32 billion (up around 10%) and earnings per share at $6.73, nearly 5% higher than in Q1 2025. ​Consensus forecasts point to Q1 earnings of roughly $6.73 per share, representing modest year-on-year growth of around 5%, alongside revenue expectations in the region of $55.46 billion, up around 31% compared to a year ago.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7e5b2042a7d8a8c6\">>>","score":0.95931095},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2fa6feadcc3dac37\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Q1 Revenue Soars 33% in Q1, Net Profit Hits $26.8 Billion Ahead of Mass Layoffs\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2fa6feadcc3dac37\">>>","url":"https://variety.com/2026/digital/news/meta-q1-2026-earnings-1236733502/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"120bcc5250e00af9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTech giant raises guidance on 2026 capital spending, fueled by AI investments, to as much as $145 billion. Even as Meta continues make money hand over fist, the tech giant is set to make a large round of layoffs to optimize operations — and as it continues to plow billions into AI projects. Meta, the parent of Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp, reported revenue of $56.3 billion for the first quarter of 2026 as ad sales were strong in the period. That’s up 33% from the year-prior period. In reporting its latest quarterly results, Meta said it continues to monitor active legal and regulatory matters, including “headwinds in the EU and the U.S. that could significantly impact our business and financial results.” The company said, “For example, we continue to see scrutiny on youth-related issues and have additional trials scheduled for this year in the U.S., which may ultimately result in a material loss.”.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"120bcc5250e00af9\">>>","score":0.94608605},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dcf1a1fe9b3f85cb\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Q1 2026 earnings report - CNBC\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dcf1a1fe9b3f85cb\">>>","url":"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/meta-q1-earnings-report-2026.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0c047f51902c1c6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe jump reflects Meta CEO [Mark Zuckerberg's](https://www.cnbc.com/mark-zuckerberg/) focus on artificial intelligence investments, which have yet to produce new revenue streams but have strengthened the company's core advertising business. Zuckerberg has spent the past three months continuing his company's deeper push into AI following a strategy shift and talent overhaul that he initiated in June with the [$14.3 billion investment in Scale AI](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/12/scale-ai-founder-wang-announces-exit-for-meta-part-of-14-billion-deal.html) and the hiring of CEO Alexandr Wang. Meta and three other hyperscalers — [Alphabet](/quotes/GOOGL/), [Amazon](/quotes/AMZN/) and [Microsoft](/quotes/MSFT/) — all reported results on Wednesday, [updating investors for](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/29/openai-looms-over-earnings-from-tech-hyperscalers.html) the first time since the U.S. began combat operations in Iran in late February. The company said last week that it's laying off about [10% of its workforce](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/23/meta-will-cut-10percent-of-workforce-as-it-pushes-more-into-ai.html), or 8,000 employees, while no longer hiring people for 6,000 open roles. Those cuts follow January's layoffs affecting about 1,000 people in the [company's Reality Labs unit](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/13/meta-lays-off-vr-employees-underscoring-zuckerbergs-pivot-to-ai.html), and another round in March targeting hundreds of staffers in areas like Facebook, global operations and sales. **WATCH**: [Retail investors are expecting strong Meta earnings, says Cboe's J.J. Kinahan](https://www.cnbc.com/video/2026/04/24/retail-investors-are-expecting-strong-meta-earnings-says-cboes-jj-kinahan.html).\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0c047f51902c1c6\">>>","score":0.9311691},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bdbb2dc84161e8c0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMeta Reports Big Revenue Jump and Projected Spending Increase\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bdbb2dc84161e8c0\">>>","url":"https://www.wsj.com/business/earnings/meta-meta-q1-2026-earnings-report-ae021875?eafs_enabled=false","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fac2d0224d14fb3b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSales grew 33% in the first quarter to $56.3 billion, but company raises capex outlook as component prices rise.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fac2d0224d14fb3b\">>>","score":0.8430832}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387565474}}
{"type":"message","id":"e19ef3d0","parentId":"09317784","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:45.476Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_3","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Marvell MRVL Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI data center\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1528,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2c64b30af9e1c8b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEarnings call transcript: Marvell Q1 2026 beats estimates, stock dips\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f2c64b30af9e1c8b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-marvell-q1-2026-beats-estimates-stock-dips-93CH-4071609\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b79679e77371c257\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[MRVL-0.12%](https://www.investing.com/equities/marvell-technology-group-ltd). According to [InvestingPro](https://www.investing.com/pro/MRVL) data, analysts expect continued sales growth this year, with revenue projected to grow by 42%. CEO Matt Murphy highlighted the company’s strong position in the AI market, stating, \\\"AI now represents the majority of our data center revenue, and we expect the relative proportion of AI-related revenue to grow further in the coming years.\\\" He also emphasized Marvell’s ability to scale, noting, \\\"We’re extremely well positioned to support designs that can really grow the company to even a much larger scale and level.\\\". Looking ahead to the second quarter, we expect this momentum to continue with data center revenue projected to grow sequentially in the mid single digit range on a percentage basis, while maintaining strong year over year growth. **Matt Murphy, Chairman and CEO, Marvell Technology**: Yeah, I think you’re seeing it in operating margin dollars flowing in, Blaine, and also in EPS, right, which still continues to grow like twice the rate of revenue at this point.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b79679e77371c257\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9560841\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eebab63436827fda\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell Technology Inc (MRVL) Q1 2026 Earnings Call Highlights: Record Revenue and Robust AI ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"eebab63436827fda\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/marvell-technology-inc-mrvl-q1-070747458.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7f1e45104c06ba97\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* [Shopping](https://shopping.yahoo.com/). + [Tech](https://shopping.yahoo.com/tech/). ### [Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/). * [My Portfolio](https://finance.yahoo.com/portfolios/). * [News](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/). + [Tech](https://finance.yahoo.com/topic/tech/). + [More Topics](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/). - [Earnings](https://finance.yahoo.com/topic/earnings/). * [Markets](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/). + [Stocks](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/). - [Most expensive](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/most-expensive-stocks/). - [Technology](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/). + [Futures](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/commodities/). + [Calendar](https://finance.yahoo.com/calendar/). - [Earnings](https://finance.yahoo.com/calendar/earnings/). * [Videos](https://finance.yahoo.com/videos/). ### [Sports](https://sports.yahoo.com/). * [Show all](https://sports.yahoo.com/). * [Tech](https://tech.yahoo.com/). + [AI](https://tech.yahoo.com/ai/). - [Business](https://tech.yahoo.com/business/). * [Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/). * [Sports](https://sports.yahoo.com/). - [Shopping](https://shopping.yahoo.com/). + [Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/). - [My portfolio](https://finance.yahoo.com/portfolios/). - [News](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/). - [Markets](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/). - [Videos](https://finance.yahoo.com/videos/). + [Sports](https://sports.yahoo.com/). - [Show all](https://sports.yahoo.com/). * [Tech](https://tech.yahoo.com/). 1. [My Portfolio](https://finance.yahoo.com/portfolios/). 2. [News](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/). 8. [Tech](https://finance.yahoo.com/topic/tech/). 2. [Earnings](https://finance.yahoo.com/topic/earnings/). 3. [Markets](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/). 1. [Stocks](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/). 8. [Most expensive](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/most-expensive-stocks/). 7. [Futures](https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/commodities/). 3. [Calendar](https://finance.yahoo.com/calendar/). 1. [Earnings](https://finance.yahoo.com/calendar/earnings/). 7. [Videos](https://finance.yahoo.com/videos/). For the complete transcript of the earnings call, please refer to the [full earnings call transcript](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/MRVL). * Marvell Technology Inc ([NASDAQ:MRVL](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/MRVL)) delivered record revenue of $1.895 billion for the first quarter of fiscal 2026, reflecting a 4% sequential increase and a strong 63% year-over-year growth. For the complete transcript of the earnings call, please refer to the [full earnings call transcript](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/MRVL). This article first appeared on [GuruFocus](https://www.gurufocus.com/news/2897750/marvell-technology-inc-mrvl-q1-2026-earnings-call-highlights-record-revenue-and-robust-ai-demand-propel-growth?r=caf6fe0e0db70d936033da5461e60141).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7f1e45104c06ba97\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9356824\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8c1804746a7dd31b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell projects strong fiscal 2028 revenue on AI-driven data center boom, shares jump\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8c1804746a7dd31b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reuters.com/technology/marvell-forecasts-first-quarter-revenue-above-estimates-2026-03-05/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f0611a7622bf17d3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). ## [Browse World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). ## [Browse Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Take Five](https://www.reuters.com/business/take-five/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). ## [Browse Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). March 5 (Reuters) - Marvell Technology [(MRVL.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/MRVL.O) forecast fiscal 2028 revenue above Wall Street ‌estimates on Thursday, signaling robust demand for custom chips and interconnect solutions used in artificial intelligence data centers, sending its shares surging 15% in extended trading. Marvell and rival Broadcom [(AVGO.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/AVGO.O) help cloud-computing companies design custom chips tailored to their data-center workloads, a fast-growing business as hyperscalers seek alternatives to Nvidia's [(NVDA.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/NVDA.O) general-purpose AI processors. Broadcom on Wednesday said it expected over [$100 billion in AI chip sales next year](https://www.reuters.com/technology/broadcom-forecasts-second-quarter-revenue-above-estimates-2026-03-04/), signaling rapid share gains in a market dominated by Nvidia, which last month reported [better-than-expected results](https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/nvidia-forecasts-first-quarter-sales-above-estimates-2026-02-25/) for the January quarter. Our Standards: [The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles., opens new tab](https://www.thomsonreuters.com/en/about-us/trust-principles.html). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). *   [Media Center, opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/media-center/). *   [](https://www.facebook.com/Reuters). *   [](https://www.instagram.com/Reuters).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f0611a7622bf17d3\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.86713725\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b7fb1ee3e51c52c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell Technology, Inc. Reports First Quarter of Fiscal Year 2026 Financial Results\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b7fb1ee3e51c52c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/marvell-technology-inc-reports-first-quarter-of-fiscal-year-2026-financial-results-302468757.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d16594f82af6eb43\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nActual events or results may differ materially from those described in this press release due to a number of risks and uncertainties, including, but not limited to: risks related to our ability to estimate customer demand and future sales accurately; our ability to define, design, develop and market products for the Artificial Intelligence (AI), Cloud, and 5G markets; risks related to our dependence on a few customers for a significant portion of our revenue, particularly as our major customers comprise an increasing percentage of our revenue, as well as risks related to a significant portion of our sales being concentrated in the data center end market; risks that our customers develop their own solutions, vertically integrate which may reduce the need for our products, or acquire fully developed solutions from third parties; our ability to secure design wins from our customers and prospective customers; the impact of international conflict (such as the current armed conflicts in the Ukraine and in Israel and the Gaza Strip) and economic volatility in either domestic or foreign markets including risks related to trade conflicts or tensions, regulations, and tariffs, including but not limited to, trade restrictions imposed on our Chinese customers; risks related to changes in general macroeconomic conditions, or expectations of such conditions, such as high or rising interest rates, macroeconomic slowdowns, recessions, inflation, and stagflation; risks related to higher inventory levels; risks related to cancellations, rescheduling or deferrals of significant customer orders or shipments, as well as the ability of our customers to manage inventory; our ability to realize the expected benefits from restructuring activities; the risk of downturns in the semiconductor industry or our customer end markets; our ability to retain and hire key personnel; risks related to our return to working full time in the office as of June 2025; cybersecurity risks; our ability to limit costs related to defective products; risks related to our debt obligations; risks related to\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d16594f82af6eb43\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8649622\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4ac19b15f84f6f5d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell Technology raises Q1 guidance on data center demand\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4ac19b15f84f6f5d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/marvell-technology-raises-q1-guidance-214300626.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bf26af13178c992a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n### [News](https://www.yahoo.com/). * [US](https://www.yahoo.com/news/us/). * [Health](https://health.yahoo.com/). * [Health](https://health.yahoo.com/). * [Shopping](https://shopping.yahoo.com/). + [Health](https://shopping.yahoo.com/health/). + [Tech](https://shopping.yahoo.com/tech/). ###