{"type":"message","id":"234c5cec","parentId":"e19ef3d0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:45.476Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_4","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Arista Networks ANET Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI networking\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1718,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d672aedf1819a9b0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nANET Q1-2026 Earnings Call - Alpha Spread\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d672aedf1819a9b0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.alphaspread.com/security/nyse/anet/investor-relations/earnings-call/q1-2026\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e213135c1a059a06\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDecide at what price you'd be comfortable buying and we'll help you stay ready. **Beat:** Arista reported Q1 revenue of $2.71 billion, up 35.1% year over year and above its $2.6 billion guide, with EPS of $0.87. **Outlook raised:** Management raised full-year 2026 revenue growth to 27.7%, or about $11.5 billion, and lifted the AI target to $3.5 billion from $3.25 billion. **Supply tight:** Management said demand is outstripping supply across wafers, chips, CPUs, optics and memory, and expects that constraint to last 1 to 2 years. **Margins pressured:** Gross margin came in at 62.4%, and the company said higher component costs and customer mix will keep margins under pressure even as it maintains its full-year range. **AI momentum:** Arista said its cloud and AI networking strategy is gaining traction, with scale-out already strong, scale-across becoming more important, and scale-up expected to emerge in 2027 and beyond. The company raised its full-year outlook because demand is running ahead of what it can supply, not because demand is weakening.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e213135c1a059a06\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9728747\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ce3eddea316f3b4c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArista Networks, Inc. Reports First Quarter 2026 Financial Results - Arista\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ce3eddea316f3b4c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.arista.com/en/company/news/press-release/24017-pr-20260505\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c59c206ccbf4ee9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Arista Networks, Inc. Reports First Quarter 2026 Financial Results. (NYSE: ANET), an industry leader in data-driven, client-to-cloud networking for large AI, data center, campus, and routing environments, today announced financial results for its first quarter ended March 31, 2026. \\\"Arista is off to a strong start in Q1 2026, with both our results and our industry-leading net promoter score,\\\" said Jayshree Ullal, Chairperson and CEO of Arista Networks. * Revenue of $2.709 billion, an increase of 8.9% compared to the fourth quarter of 2025, and an increase of 35.1% from the first quarter of 2025. * GAAP and non-GAAP operating margin of 42.7% and 47.8%, respectively, compared to GAAP and non-GAAP operating margin of 42.8% and 47.8% in the first quarter of 2025. A reconciliation of the company’s non-GAAP financial measures to their most directly comparable GAAP measures has been provided in the financial statement tables included in this press release.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c59c206ccbf4ee9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9611892\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"50dc5ecb584b5d5d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEyes Will Be on Margins and AI Bookings in $ANET's Q1 Earnings - Live: Arista Networks Is Reporting Q1 Earnings. Can $ANET Continue Its 32% YTD Rally? | 24/7 Wall St.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"50dc5ecb584b5d5d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/05/live-arista-networks-is-reporting-q1-earnings-can-anet-continue-its-32-ytd-rally/liveupdates/0/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b5eed68957c2a844\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Eyes Will Be on Margins and AI Bookings in $ANET’s Q1 Earnings. ← Back to Full Coverage: Live: Arista Networks Is Reporting Q1 Earnings. Investors are watching Arista Networks (NYSE: ANET) ahead of its Q1 2026 report at 4:05 PM EST, with expectations running high. Management expects Q1 revenue of about $2.60 billion, implying ~30% growth, while gross margin is guided to 62% to 63%, down from 65%+ levels last year. **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) is down 9.2% after posting Q1 revenue of $2.71B versus $2.62B expected and adjusted EPS of $0.87, with Q2 guided to roughly $2.8B. **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) management guided for Q2 2026 revenue of about $2.8 billion, non-GAAP operating margin of 46% to 47%, and adjusted EPS near $0.88. The post-release reaction in **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) is similar to the -8.55% Q3 2025 reaction, with the initial 9.2% drop coming despite a clean revenue beat Q3 Earnings\\\") at $2.71B versus the $2.62B Street estimates.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b5eed68957c2a844\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.95045245\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc865ac7264e661f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArista Networks, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap | AllInvestView\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cc865ac7264e661f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.allinvestview.com/earnings/ANET/q1-2026/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6062e30278371fbe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Arista Networks, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap. ANET Q1 2026  May 7, 2026. Arista's shares fell sharply by 14.8% following earnings, driven primarily by a notably cautious outlook and evident deceleration in key growth metrics despite ongoing strength in AI-driven product innovation and market share gains. * Innovation in optics (XPO form factor) and AI fabrics points to a strong product roadmap, but current execution concerns and near-term demand weakness weighed on the stock. This summary was generated by AI from the official earnings call transcript and is provided for informational purposes only. For the complete transcript and financial data, visit ANET on AllInvestView. ACEL · Q1 2026  Assurant, Inc. AIZ · Q1 2026  Astera Labs, Inc. Common Stock. ALAB · Q1 2026  Alight, Inc. ALIT · Q1 2026  AMC Entertainment Holdings, Inc. AMC · Q1 2026  Aurora Innovation Inc. Class A Common Stock. AUR · Q1 2026  Axon Enterprise, Inc. AXON · Q1 2026  Azenta Inc. AZTA · Q2 2026  The Brink's Company.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6062e30278371fbe\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9356824\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1d679e5624f99e73\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArista Networks (ANET|$217.5B) - 2026 Q1 Earnings Analysis\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1d679e5624f99e73\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OmQEqQuCjvw\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0ca49112827f4b23\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nANET Arista Networks 2026 Q1 Earnings: Arista Networks reported strong revenue growth and profitability in Q1 2026, significantly beating\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0ca49112827f4b23\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.92652357\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Arista Networks ANET Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI networking","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1718,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d672aedf1819a9b0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nANET Q1-202