 data center, campus, and routing environments, today announced financial results for its first quarter ended March 31, 2026. \"Arista is off to a strong start in Q1 2026, with both our results and our industry-leading net promoter score,\" said Jayshree Ullal, Chairperson and CEO of Arista Networks. * Revenue of $2.709 billion, an increase of 8.9% compared to the fourth quarter of 2025, and an increase of 35.1% from the first quarter of 2025. * GAAP and non-GAAP operating margin of 42.7% and 47.8%, respectively, compared to GAAP and non-GAAP operating margin of 42.8% and 47.8% in the first quarter of 2025. A reconciliation of the company’s non-GAAP financial measures to their most directly comparable GAAP measures has been provided in the financial statement tables included in this press release.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9c59c206ccbf4ee9\">>>","score":0.9611892},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"50dc5ecb584b5d5d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEyes Will Be on Margins and AI Bookings in $ANET's Q1 Earnings - Live: Arista Networks Is Reporting Q1 Earnings. Can $ANET Continue Its 32% YTD Rally? | 24/7 Wall St.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"50dc5ecb584b5d5d\">>>","url":"https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/05/05/live-arista-networks-is-reporting-q1-earnings-can-anet-continue-its-32-ytd-rally/liveupdates/0/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b5eed68957c2a844\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Eyes Will Be on Margins and AI Bookings in $ANET’s Q1 Earnings. ← Back to Full Coverage: Live: Arista Networks Is Reporting Q1 Earnings. Investors are watching Arista Networks (NYSE: ANET) ahead of its Q1 2026 report at 4:05 PM EST, with expectations running high. Management expects Q1 revenue of about $2.60 billion, implying ~30% growth, while gross margin is guided to 62% to 63%, down from 65%+ levels last year. **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) is down 9.2% after posting Q1 revenue of $2.71B versus $2.62B expected and adjusted EPS of $0.87, with Q2 guided to roughly $2.8B. **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) management guided for Q2 2026 revenue of about $2.8 billion, non-GAAP operating margin of 46% to 47%, and adjusted EPS near $0.88. The post-release reaction in **Arista Networks** (NYSE:ANET) is similar to the -8.55% Q3 2025 reaction, with the initial 9.2% drop coming despite a clean revenue beat Q3 Earnings\") at $2.71B versus the $2.62B Street estimates.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b5eed68957c2a844\">>>","score":0.95045245},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc865ac7264e661f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nArista Networks, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap | AllInvestView\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cc865ac7264e661f\">>>","url":"https://www.allinvestview.com/earnings/ANET/q1-2026/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6062e30278371fbe\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Arista Networks, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap. ANET Q1 2026  May 7, 2026. Arista's shares fell sharply by 14.8% following earnings, driven primarily by a notably cautious outlook and evident deceleration in key growth metrics despite ongoing strength in AI-driven product innovation and market share gains. * Innovation in optics (XPO form factor) and AI fabrics points to a strong product roadmap, but current execution concerns and near-term demand weakness weighed on the stock. This summary was generated by AI from the official earnings call transcript and is provided for informational purposes only. For the complete transcript and financial data, visit ANET on AllInvestView. ACEL · Q1 2026  Assurant, Inc. AIZ · Q1 2026  Astera Labs, Inc. Common Stock. ALAB · Q1 2026  Alight, Inc. ALIT · Q1 2026  AMC Entertainment Holdings, Inc. AMC · Q1 2026  Aurora Innovation Inc. Class A Common Stock. AUR · Q1 2026  Axon Enterprise, Inc. AXON · Q1 2026  Azenta Inc. AZTA · Q2 2026  The Brink's Company.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6062e30278371fbe\">>>","score":0.9356824},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1d679e5624f99e73\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nArista Networks (ANET|$217.5B) - 2026 Q1 Earnings Analysis\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1d679e5624f99e73\">>>","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OmQEqQuCjvw","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0ca49112827f4b23\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nANET Arista Networks 2026 Q1 Earnings: Arista Networks reported strong revenue growth and profitability in Q1 2026, significantly beating\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0ca49112827f4b23\">>>","score":0.92652357}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387565475}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9ca1c71","parentId":"234c5cec","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:32:45.477Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d5copst2gfrn_5","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Eaton ETN Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center power\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1667,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"22564ee806c63eee\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEaton (ETN) Posts Record Q1 Revenue as Electrical Backlog ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"22564ee806c63eee\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://news.alphastreet.com/eaton-etn-posts-record-q1-revenue-as-electrical-backlog-surges-48-on-data-center-demand/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d3446f6905fdc7f1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Eaton (ETN) Posts Record Q1 Revenue as Electrical Backlog Surges 48% on Data Center Demand. Eaton Corporation (ETN) delivered a first-quarter record across nearly every financial metric on May 5, 2026, posting revenue of $7.5 billion and adjusted earnings per share of $2.81 — both first-quarter highs for the intelligent power management company. The results came in above the high end of guidance on organic growth and segment margins, reflecting surging demand from data center buildout and sustained aerospace and industrial momentum. Yet despite the beat, Eaton shares fell approximately 3% on the day, as investors focused on near-term segment margin compression tied to the $11 billion in acquisitions closed during the quarter. Eaton reported Q1 2026 revenue of $7.5 billion, up 17% from the first quarter of 2025, driven by three growth components: organic sales growth of 10%, acquisition-related contributions of 4%, and foreign exchange tailwinds of 3% (Eaton Q1 2026 Earnings Press Release, BusinessWire, May 5, 2026).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d3446f6905fdc7f1\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.97231245\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dd8ebbd2a3dac40e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEaton Earnings Call Highlights Data Center Supercycle - The Globe and Mail\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dd8ebbd2a3dac40e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/markets/stocks/ETN/pressreleases/1758738/eaton-earnings-call-highlights-data-center-supercycle/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2b2becd763c077d6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRead on for the main highlights of the call. Eaton Corporation’s latest earnings call carried an upbeat tone, with management leaning heavily into record results and a powerful demand backdrop, especially in electrification and data centers. Executives acknowledged short‑term margin pressure and ramp‑up costs but framed them as temporary, while emphasizing a clear path to higher profitability and sustained double‑digit organic growth into 2026 and beyond. On the call, management raised its 2026 total‑company organic growth outlook by 200 basis points to a 9%–11% range, with a midpoint of about 10%, signaling confidence that current trends are sustainable rather than a short‑lived surge. Eaton’s total electrical backlog swelled about 48% year over year, with electrical sector orders up 47% in the quarter, pointing to multi‑year revenue visibility. The company reaffirmed its cash‑flow expectations for the year and lifted 2026 adjusted EPS guidance to a range of $13.05 to $13.50, with the midpoint of $13.28 incorporating both Q1 outperformance and near‑term acquisition dilution.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2b2becd763c077d6\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9274752\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6535cb0b460585c6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEaton Corp Q1 FY26 Earnings Call | $ETN | WATCH LIVE - YouTube\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6535cb0b460585c6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orzl68k7vF0\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c96565f39e67ef12\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n. $2.73) — inline Revenue: $7.45B (est. $7.13B) — inline Reported: 2026 ... data centers, utilities, and commercial and residential\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c96565f39e67ef12\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8967681\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc1a8567e118425e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEaton (ETN) boosts growth with $11B deals and higher debt in Q1 ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc1a8567e118425e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/ETN/10-q-eaton-corp-plc-quarterly-earnings-report-f357b7eecf1f.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5009377c41f30c2f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n**Eaton Corporation plc** reported first-quarter 2026 net sales of **$7.45 billion**, up 17% from 2025, driven by strong Electrical and Aerospace demand and recent acquisitions. Net income attributable to ordinary shareholders fell to **$866 million** and diluted EPS to **$2.22**, mainly from higher interest, amortization, restructuring, and deal costs. **Adjusted earnings**, which exclude acquisition, restructuring and amortization items, rose to **$1.09 billion**, with adjusted EPS of **$2.81**, modestly above 2025. The company plans to spin off its **Mobility** segment as a separate public company by the end of the first quarter of 2027, subject to approvals, and continues a multi‑year restructuring program with total expected charges of **$475 million**. * **Robust revenue and backlog growth:** Net sales increased 17% year over year to $7.45 billion, with strong organic growth in Electrical and Aerospace, and total backlog reached about $22.8 billion, with roughly 68% targeted for delivery within the next 12 months.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5009377c41f30c2f\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8351749\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee106de21cb06aec\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEaton Reports Record First Quarter 2026 Results, with Accelerating ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee106de21cb06aec\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.eaton.com/us/en-us/company/news-insights/news-releases/2026/eaton-reports-record-first-quarter-2026-results.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ebeb69001340896d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# **Eaton Reports Record First Quarter 2026 Results, with Accelerating Growth in Sales, Orders and Backlog, and Raises 2026 Organic Growth Guidance to 10% from 8% at the Midpoint**. * **First quarter sales were up 17% with organic sales growth of 10%, above the high end of the 5-7% guidance range**. * **For full year 2026, earnings per share expected to be between $10.88 and $11.33, up 6% at the midpoint over 2025, and adjusted earnings per share expected to be between $13.05 and $13.50​, up 10% at the midpoint over 2025**. Sales in the quarter were $7.5 billion, a record and up 17% from the first quarter of 2025. Sales for the Electrical Americas segment were a record $3.6 billion, up 20% from the first quarter of 2025. Operating profits were a first quarter record $922 million, up 2% over the first quarter of 2025, and operating margins in the quarter were 25.6%. Sales for the Electrical Global segment were a record $1.9 billion, up 21% from the first quarter of 2025.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ebeb69001340896d\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.829285\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Eaton ETN Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center power","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1667,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"22564ee806c63eee\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEaton (ETN) Posts Record Q1 Revenue as Electrical Backlog ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"22564ee806c63eee\">>>","url":"https://news.alphastreet.com/eaton-etn-posts-record-q1-revenue-as-electrical-backlog-surges-48-on-data-center-demand/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3446f6905fdc7f1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Eaton (ETN) Posts Record Q1 Revenue as Electrical Backlog Surges 48% on Data Center Demand. Eaton Corporation (ETN) delivered a first-quarter record across nearly every financial metric on May 5, 2026, posting revenue of $7.5 billion and adjusted earnings per share of $2.81 — both first-quarter highs for the intelligent power management company. The results came in above the high end of guidance on organic growth and segment margins, reflecting surging demand from data center buildout and sustained aerospace and industrial momentum. Yet despite the beat, Eaton shares fell approximately 3% on the day, as investors focused on near-term segment margin compression tied to the $11 billion in acquisitions closed during the quarter. Eaton reported Q1 2026 revenue of $7.5 billion, up 17% from the first quarter of 2025, driven by three growth components: organic sales growth of 10%, acquisition-related contributions of 4%, and foreign exchange tailwinds of 3% (Eaton Q1 2026 Earnings Press Release, BusinessWire, May 5, 2026).\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d3446f6905fdc7f1\">>>","score":0.97231245},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dd8ebbd2a3dac40e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEaton Earnings Call Highlights Data Center Supercycle - The Globe and Mail\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dd8ebbd2a3dac40e\">>>","url":"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/markets/stocks/ETN/pressreleases/1758738/eaton-earnings-call-highlights-data-center-supercycle/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2b2becd763c077d6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRead on for the main highlights of the call. Eaton Corporation’s latest earnings call carried an upbeat tone, with management leaning heavily into record results and a powerful demand backdrop, especially in electrification and data centers. Executives acknowledged short‑term margin pressure and ramp‑up costs but framed them as temporary, while emphasizing a clear path to higher profitability and sustained double‑digit organic growth into 2026 and beyond. On the call, management raised its 2026 total‑company organic growth outlook by 200 basis points to a 9%–11% range, with a midpoint of about 10%, signaling confidence that current trends are sustainable rather than a short‑lived surge. Eaton’s total electrical backlog swelled about 48% year over year, with electrical sector orders up 47% in the quarter, pointing to multi‑year revenue visibility. The company reaffirmed its cash‑flow expectations for the year and lifted 2026 adjusted EPS guidance to a range of $13.05 to $13.50, with the midpoint of $13.28 incorporating both Q1 outperformance and near‑term acquisition dilution.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2b2becd763c077d6\">>>","score":0.9274752},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6535cb0b460585c6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEaton Corp Q1 FY26 Earnings Call | $ETN | WATCH LIVE - YouTube\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6535cb0b460585c6\">>>","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orzl68k7vF0","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c96565f39e67ef12\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n. $2.73) — inline Revenue: $7.45B (est. $7.13B) — inline Reported: 2026 ... data centers, utilities, and commercial and residential\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c96565f39e67ef12\">>>","score":0.8967681},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"bc1a8567e118425e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEaton (ETN) boosts growth with $11B d