{"type":"message","id":"58779d93","parentId":"e0b6558a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:01.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pzmhd93ygsp1_4","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"CrowdStrike CRWD Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI cybersecurity\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2152,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d630e58435df54d9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCrowdStrike Q1 FY2026 slides: revenue growth strong at 22%, margins contract By Investing.com\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d630e58435df54d9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/crowdstrike-q1-fy2026-slides-revenue-growth-strong-at-22-margins-contract-93CH-4079049\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e9f2a252147a73eb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n(NASDAQ:CRWD) presented its Q1 FY2026 financial results on June 3, 2025, highlighting continued strong revenue growth while showing some margin compression compared to the prior year. CrowdStrike reported solid financial results for the first quarter of fiscal year 2026, with annual recurring revenue (ARR) reaching $4.44 billion, representing a 22% year-over-year increase. Total revenue grew to $1.103 billion, up from $921 million in Q1 FY2025, while subscription revenue increased to $1.051 billion from $872 million in the same period last year. CrowdStrike’s Flex (NASDAQ:FLEX) model continues to drive platform adoption, with accounts that have adopted Flex now representing more than $3.2 billion in total deal value. CrowdStrike’s AI-native security platform is positioned to address a total addressable market (TAM) of $116 billion in calendar year 2025, with projections showing expansion to $250 billion by 2029. For Q2 FY2026, CrowdStrike provided guidance for total revenue between $1.144 billion and $1.152 billion, with non-GAAP operating income expected to range from $226.9 million to $233.1 million.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e9f2a252147a73eb\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.96264863\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a5e240a837578f0f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCrowdStrike (CRWD) Q1 2026 Earnings Transcript\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a5e240a837578f0f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2025/06/03/crowdstrike-crwd-q1-2026-earnings-transcript/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3fe53a94d08727d7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGeorge Kurtz said, \\\"Falcon Flex is significantly evolving our go-to-market and customer experience.\\\" with over $3.2 billion in closed deal value across more than 820 accounts (non-GAAP) as of Q1 FY2026, and ongoing rapid adoption. Highlights include: one, Q1 net new ARR of $194 million, double-digit millions ahead of our expectations; two, Q1 ending ARR surpassing $4.4 billion, maintaining our leadership as the only pure-play cybersecurity software company of this size; three, subscription gross margin of 80%, demonstrating our AI platform efficiency; four, sustained 97% gross retention as customers remain firmly committed to Falcon; five, free cash flow of $279 million or 25% of revenue, demonstrating double-digit quarter-on-quarter growth; and six, added $774 million of total FalconFlex account value, bringing the total deal value of accounts that have adopted FalconFlex to $3.2 billion, growing 31% sequentially and more than six times year over year.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3fe53a94d08727d7\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.94263905\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edc64f30a55bee11\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCrowdStrike shares drop on weak revenue guidance - CNBC\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edc64f30a55bee11\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/03/crowdstrike-crwd-q1-earnings-report-2026.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a4da50642ebc8d9a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Tech](https://www.cnbc.com/technology/). Revenue increased nearly 20% in the fiscal first quarter, which ended on April 30, according to a [statement](https://ir.crowdstrike.com/news-releases/news-release-details/crowdstrike-reports-first-quarter-fiscal-year-2026-financial). Costs rose in sales and marketing as well as in research and development and administration, partly because of a [broad software outage](https://www.cnbc.com/2024/10/25/delta-suit-against-crowdstrike-after-it-outage-caused-cancellations.html) last summer. For the current quarter, CrowdStrike called for 82 cents to 84 cents in adjusted earnings per share on $1.14 billion to $1.15 billion in revenue. Analysts polled by LSEG were expecting 81 cents in earnings per share and $1.16 billion in revenue. In May, CrowdStrike said it would [cut 500 employees](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/05/07/crowdstrike-announces-5percent-job-cuts-says-ai-reshaping-every-industry.html), which works out to around 5% of its workforce. * [Trump's $100,000 visa plan could hit these companies the hardest](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/09/22/trumps-100000-visa-plan-could-hit-these-companies-the-hardest.html). * [Goldman Sachs raises S&P 500 target for year-end](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/09/22/goldman-sachs-raises-sp-500-target-for-year-end.html). Here are homegrown tech plays to watch](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/09/21/china-isnt-begging-nvidia-anymore-watch-homegrown-tech-plays-instead.html). **WATCH:** [Trade Tracker: Malcolm Ethridge buys more CrowdStrike, Palo Alto Networks, Spotify and Oracle](https://www.cnbc.com/video/2025/03/28/trade-tracker-malcolm-ethridge-buys-more-crowdstrike-palo-alto-networks-spotify-and-oracle.html). [Halftime Report](https://www.cnbc.com/halftime/). [Choose CNBC as your preferred source on Google and never miss a moment from the most trusted name in business news.](https://www.google.com/preferences/source?q=https://www.cnbc.com/).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a4da50642ebc8d9a\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.88705814\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ea047622be7f4b66\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCrowdStrike Reports First Quarter Fiscal Year 2026 Financial Results | CrowdStrike Holdings, Inc.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ea047622be7f4b66\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://ir.crowdstrike.com/news-releases/news-release-details/crowdstrike-reports-first-quarter-fiscal-year-2026-financial\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4ac3192540c336d0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* **Revenue:** Total revenue was $1.10 billion, a 20% increase, compared to $921.0 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. Subscription revenue was $1.05 billion, a 20% increase, compared to $872.2 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. * **Income/Loss from Operations:** GAAP loss from operations was $124.7 million, compared to GAAP income from operations of $6.9 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. Non-GAAP income from operations was $201.1 million, compared to $213.3 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. * **Net Income/Loss Attributable to****CrowdStrike****:** GAAP net loss attributable to CrowdStrike was $110.2 million, compared to GAAP net income attributable to CrowdStrike of $42.8 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. GAAP net loss per share attributable to CrowdStrike, diluted, was $0.44, compared to GAAP net income per share attributable to CrowdStrike, diluted, of $0.17 in the first quarter of fiscal 2025. Non-GAAP net income attributable to CrowdStrike was $184.7 million, compared to $196.8 million in the first quarter of fiscal 2025.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4ac3192540c336d0\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8825193\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6f16f96df9ec96ca\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCrowdStrike (CRWD) Earnings Report Q1 2026 | Beat, EPS & Revenue | 24/7 Wall St.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6f16f96df9ec96ca\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://247wallst.com/companies/crwd/earnings/2026/Q1\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"18d69c8018ea2f96\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# CRWD Q1 2026 Q4 2026 Q3 2026 Q2 2026 Q1 2026 Q4 2025 Q3 2025 Q2 2025 Q1 2025 Earnings. CrowdStrike delivered a mixed but broadly resilient fiscal first quarter, posting non-GAAP diluted EPS of $0.73 that beat the $0.66 consensus estimate by 10.62%, even as revenue of $1.10 billion came in fractionally light of the $1.11 billion Wall St… Read more CrowdStrike delivered a mixed but broadly resilient fiscal first quarter, posting non-GAAP diluted EPS of $0.73 that beat the $0.66 consensus estimate by 10.62%, even as revenue of $1.10 billion came in fractionally light of the $1.11 billion Wall Street expected, growing 19.8% year over year. Looking ahead, CrowdStrike guided Q2 non-GAAP EPS of $0.82 to $0.84 on revenue of $1.14 billion to $1.15 billion, with management expressing conviction in net new ARR re-acceleration and margin expansion in the second half of fiscal 2026. Q1 2026 vs Q1 2025, source: SEC Filings.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"18d69c8018ea2f96\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8652358\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["query","provider","count","tookMs","externalContent","results"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387581594}}
{"type":"message","id":"c52ea04e","parentId":"58779d93","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:01.596Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pzmhd93ygsp1_5","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Super Micro Computer SMCI Q3 2026 earnings revenue audit\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2090,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0667aefecd10da8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSupermicro (SMCI|$16.2B) - 2026 Q3 Earnings Analysis - YouTube\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0667aefecd10da8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X0tavQR5Two\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"24fdbb373707727d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSMCI Supermicro 2026 Q3 Earnings: Supermicro reported strong revenue growth and exceeded EPS expectations in Q3 2026.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"24fdbb373707727d\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999974\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2963dd7b85fc79bd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSuper Micro (SMCI) Q3 2026 Earnings Transcript | The Motley Fool\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2963dd7b85fc79bd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/05/05/super-micro-smci-q3-2026-earnings-transcript/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"81a0e2896677eb97\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* **Revenue** -- **Super Micro Computer** ([SMCI](/quote/nasdaq/smci/) +24.38%) reported $10.2 billion, reflecting a 123% increase year over year and a 19% decline quarter over quarter, attributed to component shortages and customer site readiness delays. * **Non-GAAP Gross Margin** -- 10.1%, representing a 58% sequential improvement from 6.4% last quarter, driven by improved customer and product mix, and reduced tariffs, expedite, and inventory reserve charges. Please note that some of the information you will hear during our discussion today will consist of forward-looking statements, including, without limitation, those regarding revenue, gross margin, operating expenses, other income and expenses, taxes, capital allocation, and future business outlook, including guidance for the fourth quarter of 2026 and the full fiscal year 2026. As Charles mentioned, we have a large number of large deals from new NeoClouds and cloud service providers, which we expect to increase our footprint and customer diversity as well as our margins, along with our DCBPS and enterprise expansion.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"81a0e2896677eb97\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99999344\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f8e422121be7c2c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSuper Micro Computer Stock Surged 20% After Q3 2026 Earnings. Here’s What Drove the Margin Comeback | TIKR.com\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f8e422121be7c2c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.tikr.com/blog/super-micro-computer-stock-surged-20-after-q3-2026-earnings-heres-what-drove-the-margin-comeback\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"29d4551351348dd0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Super Micro Computer Stock Surged 20% After Q3 2026 Earnings. Here’s What Drove the Margin Comeback. * **Earnings Reaction:** ~+20% after-hours (May 5, 2026). **Super Micro Computer (****SMCI****)** shares jumped roughly 20% in after-hours trading on May 5, 2026, reclaiming $33, even as the company missed revenue estimates by more than $2.2 billion. Bulls are pointing to a gross margin recovery that came in nearly 50% above what analysts expected. Bears are pointing to a $7.5 billion net debt position, a cash conversion cycle that doubled in one quarter, and a class action lawsuit with a lead plaintiff deadline on May 26. Non-GAAP gross margin came in at 10.1%, a 58% sequential improvement from 6.4% in Q2, well above the 6.75% analysts expected. Super Micro Computer Gross Margin Target **(TIKR)**. ******See historical and forward estimates for Super Micro Computer stock (It’s free!) >>>******.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"29d4551351348dd0\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999739\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"02b43ac88db21d53\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSuper Micro (SMCI) Q3 earnings report 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"02b43ac88db21d53\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/05/super-micro-smci-q3-earnings-report-2026.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39838ea62bf4b077\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* The server maker said in March it severed ties with a co-founder who was named in a federal indictment in March. Super Micro Computer shares jumped 19% in extended trading on Tuesday after the server maker issued strong guidance, although revenue for its fiscal third quarter came in below estimates. For the fiscal fourth quarter, management called for 65 cents to 69 cents in adjusted earnings per share on $11 billion to $12.5 billion in revenue. The LSEG consensus was for earnings of 55 cents per share and $11.07 billion in revenue. The indictment did not name Super Micro, but the company said one defendant was a co-founder and executive, another was a manager, and the third was a contractor. CEO Charles Liang told investors in March, \\\"It appears that Supermicro has been a victim of the elaborate schemes orchestrated by these individuals, which deceived both federal authorities and our internal compliance team.\\\" Wally Liaw, the co-founder and executive described in the indictment, no longer has any relationship to the company and left the board, Liang wrote.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39838ea62bf4b077\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999683\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a79212ac73b0c466\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSuper Micro Computer, Inc. Q3 2026 Earnings Call Summary\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a79212ac73b0c466\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/super-micro-computer-inc-q3-123000764.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"72164ac4e5eeffb8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRevenue of $10.2 billion was impacted by customer site readiness delays, specifically power and networking constraints at cloud deployment\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"72164ac4e5eeffb8\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99995315\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Super Micro Computer SMCI Q3 2026 earnings revenue audit","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":2090,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0667aefecd10da8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSupermicro (SMCI|$16.2B) - 2026 Q3 Earnings Analysis - YouTube\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0667aefecd10da8\">>>","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X0tavQR5Two","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"24fdbb373707727d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSMCI Supermicro 2026 Q3 Earnings: Supermicro reported strong revenue growth and exceeded EPS expectations in Q3 2026.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"24fdbb373707727d\">>>","score":0.9999974},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2963dd7b85fc79bd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSuper Micro (SMCI) Q3 2026 Earnings Transcript | The Motley Fool\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2963dd7b85fc79bd\">>>","url":"https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/05/05/super-micro-smci-q3-2026-earnings-transcript/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONT