ming $33, even as the company missed revenue estimates by more than $2.2 billion. Bulls are pointing to a gross margin recovery that came in nearly 50% above what analysts expected. Bears are pointing to a $7.5 billion net debt position, a cash conversion cycle that doubled in one quarter, and a class action lawsuit with a lead plaintiff deadline on May 26. Non-GAAP gross margin came in at 10.1%, a 58% sequential improvement from 6.4% in Q2, well above the 6.75% analysts expected. Super Micro Computer Gross Margin Target **(TIKR)**. ******See historical and forward estimates for Super Micro Computer stock (It’s free!) >>>******.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"29d4551351348dd0\">>>","score":0.9999739},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"02b43ac88db21d53\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSuper Micro (SMCI) Q3 earnings report 2026\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"02b43ac88db21d53\">>>","url":"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/05/super-micro-smci-q3-earnings-report-2026.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39838ea62bf4b077\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n* The server maker said in March it severed ties with a co-founder who was named in a federal indictment in March. Super Micro Computer shares jumped 19% in extended trading on Tuesday after the server maker issued strong guidance, although revenue for its fiscal third quarter came in below estimates. For the fiscal fourth quarter, management called for 65 cents to 69 cents in adjusted earnings per share on $11 billion to $12.5 billion in revenue. The LSEG consensus was for earnings of 55 cents per share and $11.07 billion in revenue. The indictment did not name Super Micro, but the company said one defendant was a co-founder and executive, another was a manager, and the third was a contractor. CEO Charles Liang told investors in March, \"It appears that Supermicro has been a victim of the elaborate schemes orchestrated by these individuals, which deceived both federal authorities and our internal compliance team.\" Wally Liaw, the co-founder and executive described in the indictment, no longer has any relationship to the company and left the board, Liang wrote.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39838ea62bf4b077\">>>","score":0.9999683},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a79212ac73b0c466\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSuper Micro Computer, Inc. Q3 2026 Earnings Call Summary\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a79212ac73b0c466\">>>","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/super-micro-computer-inc-q3-123000764.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"72164ac4e5eeffb8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRevenue of $10.2 billion was impacted by customer site readiness delays, specifically power and networking constraints at cloud deployment\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"72164ac4e5eeffb8\">>>","score":0.99995315}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387581594}}
{"type":"message","id":"139a61a1","parentId":"c52ea04e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:11.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough data for most of the stocks. Let me also search for the remaining ones: INTC, ARM, STX, BE, VST, NEE, TSM.\n","thinkingSignature":"5552b275181580d104759754c1764ad3f6ecd528e3284319204b2b991a2d3673"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Intel INTC Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center turnaround"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Seagate STX Q3 2026 earnings revenue AI storage"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_3","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Bloom Energy BE Q1 2026 earnings revenue fuel cell data center"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_4","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"Vistra VST Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI data center power"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_5","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"TSMC TSM Q1 2026 earnings revenue advanced packaging CoWoS"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9218,"output":262,"cacheRead":69536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79016,"cost":{"input":0.0027654,"output":0.0003144,"cacheRead":0.004172159999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007251959999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778387581596,"responseId":"064f3d802d300d2ce09248381ba84baa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3919787f","parentId":"139a61a1","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:15.107Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Intel INTC Q1 2026 earnings revenue data center turnaround\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1627,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef50ced9276525a8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel Q1 2026 earnings beat on data center, AI demand - Quartz\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef50ced9276525a8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://qz.com/intel-q1-2026-earnings-data-center-ai-revenue-042326\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"769b506c2ba881fb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel's data center and AI revenue jumps 22% as quarterly sales top Wall Street estimates · The chipmaker posted $13.6 billion in Q1 revenue,\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"769b506c2ba881fb\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999938\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ab0e89b0359940c7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel's Q1 2026: Revenue Up, But Is the Market Pricing a Turnaround?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ab0e89b0359940c7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/engineering-decoded_intel-is-up-nearly-300-the-fundamentals-activity-7454420057775845376-ojUJ\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"892b28925f380bb8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRevenue came in at $13.6B, up 7% year-over-year. Non-GAAP gross margins expanded to about 41%. Data Center and AI was the genuine bright spot:\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"892b28925f380bb8\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.999992\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"03928a0333903d8d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel (INTC) Q1 2026 Earnings Breakdown: Stock Soars 15% on AI ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"03928a0333903d8d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BLBxIogfNYs\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bbd02c2c3f4c3122\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel (INTC) Q1 2026 Earnings Breakdown: Stock Soars 15% on AI CPU Demand!** Intel Corporation just released its Q1 2026 earnings,\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bbd02c2c3f4c3122\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99990237\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d6ac55f3b3308c3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIntel Q1 2026 Earnings: $13.6B Revenue, DCAI Up 22%\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d6ac55f3b3308c3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"47ae2d98889cc8b5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n1.   [Data Center and AI: The 22% Surge](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/#toc-2). 2.   [Intel Foundry: The 16% Vindication](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/#toc-3). 3.   [Lip-Bu Tan’s First Full-Quarter Scorecard](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/#toc-4). 4.   [How Intel’s Q1 Stacks Up Against AMD, Nvidia, and TSMC](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/#toc-5). 5.   [Intel Foundry, TSMC, and the US Government’s 10% Stake](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13-6-billion-revenue-data-center-surge/#toc-6). 6.   [The 18A Node Finally Reaches High-Volume Manufacturing](https://tech-insider.org/intel-q1-2026-earnings-13