urce: Web Search\n---\n# Seagate Technology plc Q3 2026 Earnings Recap. STX Q3 2026  April 29, 2026. Seagate shares surged 8% after the company’s fiscal Q3 report, as revenue jumped 44% year-over-year, gross margins hit all-time highs, and management issued notably upbeat guidance. Investors responded positively to record free cash flow and strong commentary on accelerating storage demand tied to AI and cloud infrastructure buildout. This summary was generated by AI from the official earnings call transcript and is provided for informational purposes only. For the complete transcript and financial data, visit STX on AllInvestView. ## Also Reported on April 29, 2026. AB · Q1 2026  Amkor Technology, Inc. AMKR · Q1 2026  ArcBest Corporation. Track Seagate Technology plc in your portfolio with real-time analytics, dividend tracking, and more. AllInvestView is not a registered investment advisor or broker/dealer, and the information presented here is for educational and informational purposes only.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0b49afbd377c38b5\">>>","score":0.9999844},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d7afa0dfd1e60cca\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSTX Q3-2026 Earnings Call\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d7afa0dfd1e60cca\">>>","url":"https://www.alphaspread.com/security/nasdaq/stx/investor-relations/earnings-call/q3-2026","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a2b160d02872b803\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n**Strong quarter:** Seagate said March quarter revenue was $3.1 billion, up 44% year over year, with record gross margin, more than doubled operating income, and free cash flow close to $1 billion. **HAMR ramp:** Seagate said Mozaic 4 is now shipping, two of the world’s largest cloud providers are qualified on the 4+ terabyte per disk product, and the company expects Mozaic 4 to become a majority of HAMR exabyte shipments exiting calendar 2026. Mozaic 4 began revenue shipments in late March, two large cloud customers are qualified on the 4+ terabyte per disk product, and the company expects Mozaic 4 to be the majority of HAMR exabyte shipments exiting calendar 2026. The company said most of its nearline capacity is allocated over the next four quarters and that build-to-order contracts for fiscal 2027 have been finalized, giving it strong visibility into mix, volume and pricing.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a2b160d02872b803\">>>","score":0.99996054}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387595106}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c8a2301","parentId":"ba322d5b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:15.107Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_3","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Bloom Energy BE Q1 2026 earnings revenue fuel cell data center\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1557,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"240e2e7940356100\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy Q1 Revenue Doubling Validates Data Center Power Solution Growth Expectations; Shares Surge Over 16% Post-Market\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"240e2e7940356100\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261834375-be-orcl-oracle-interest-stock-datacenter-nasdaq-tradingkey\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c79d445253b609f0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Bloom Energy Q1 Revenue Doubling Validates Data Center Power Solution Growth Expectations; Shares Surge Over 16% Post-Market. Bloom Energy reported Q1 2026 non-GAAP revenue of $751 million, up 130.4% year-over-year, beating expectations. The company raised full-year revenue guidance to $3.4 billion–$3.8 billion and expects gross margin around 34% by 2026. During the period, Bloom Energy's non-GAAP revenue reached $751 million, a significant year-over-year increase of 130.4%, surpassing the market expectation of $540 million. Regarding specific business segments, product revenue was recorded at $653 million, a 208.4% increase from $211.9 million in the same period last year and a slight 2.33% increase quarter-over-quarter; installation revenue was $25.931 million, down 22.94% year-over-year; service revenue reached $61.879 million, up 15.56% year-over-year; and electricity revenue was $9.896 million, a year-over-year decline of 63.28%. The most striking data point in this earnings report is the substantial growth in product revenue; this quarter, the company's product revenue surged 208.37% year-over-year to $653 million, accounting for 86.99% of total revenue.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c79d445253b609f0\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9565735\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5ab4ffd797e251a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy Q1 Earnings Call Highlights\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5ab4ffd797e251a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/bloom-energy-q1-earnings-call-003711170.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4481e29810c6baec\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n- Best gifts for sister-in-law. - Best gifts for mother-in-law. * Bloom delivered a “record” Q1 with **$751.1 million revenue (+130% YoY)**, expanded gross margin (31.5%), positive operating cash flow ($73.6M), and management raised full‑year 2026 revenue guidance to **$3.4–$3.8 billion** with upgraded profitability targets. * Demand from AI data centers is a major growth driver — Oracle’s Project Jupiter plans to replace turbines and diesel with **up to 2.45 GW** of Bloom Energy Servers, and Bloom says more than half of its current data‑center backlog comes from hyperscalers, neoclouds, and colocators building islanded microgrids. Bloom Energy (NYSE:BE) reported what founder, chairman, and CEO KR Sridhar called a “record first quarter,” with revenue, gross margin, and operating income coming in “materially above our prior outlook.” Management raised full-year 2026 guidance, citing accelerating demand for clean, reliable on-site power—particularly from AI data center customers—and confidence in Bloom’s ability to scale manufacturing capacity quickly.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4481e29810c6baec\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.94911116\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dfa9dd22c5650788\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy Soars Past $240 as AI Data Center Deals Fuel 130% Revenue Surge — BigGo Finance\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dfa9dd22c5650788\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.biggo.com/news/Yszb2Z0BNl__-4_GtS21\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"857efaa2b477f3b3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy reported first-quarter revenue of $751.1 million, a 130% year-over-year surge that crushed consensus estimates, and swung to a GAAP profit of $70.7 million from a year-ago loss. The company lifted its full-year 2026 revenue guidance to $3.4 billion to $3.8 billion, implying roughly 80% growth at the midpoint and placing the lower bound above the old upper bound. CEO KR Sridhar declared the company is rapidly becoming the standard for on-site data center power, noting that more than half of Bloom's data center backlog comes from customers other than Oracle. Bloom is rapidly becoming the standard and 'go-to choice' for on-site power.\\\" The statement landed with force because it arrived just one day after Oracle (ORCL) and BorderPlex Digital Assets confirmed that Project Jupiter—a multi-billion-dollar AI data center campus in New Mexico—will scrap previously planned gas turbines and diesel generators in favor of up to 2.45 gigawatts of Bloom's solid oxide fuel cell systems, making it one of the largest data center microgrids in the United States.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"857efaa2b477f3b3\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.94301796\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5bc211cd51e30b5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy Q1 2026 Earnings Call Revenue Up 130% As Data ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c5bc211cd51e30b5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YEPJcscLVfA\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"473a6942e8454b17\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy Q1 2026 Earnings Call Revenue Up 130% As Data Center Demand Drives Record Product Sales · Comments.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"473a6942e8454b17\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8934678\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3a33bedac5611ebb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBloom Energy - Bloom Energy Reports Record First Quarter 2026 Results and Raises Full Year 2026 Guidance\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3a33bedac5611ebb\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://investor.bloomenergy.com/press-releases/press-release-details/2026/Bloom-Energy-Reports-Record-First-Quarter-2026-Results-and-Raises-Full-Year-2026-Guidance/default.aspx\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b5fc1fdcbe0bbf44\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTo supplement Bloom Energy condensed consolidated financial statement information presented on a GAAP basis, Bloom Energy provides financial measures including non-GAAP gross profit, non-GAAP gross margin, non-GAAP operating income (non-GAAP earnings from operations), non-GAAP operating margin, non-GAAP net profit (non-GAAP net earnings), non-GAAP basic and diluted earnings per share and Adjusted EBITDA. Bloom Energy believes that providing financial measures including non-GAAP gross profit, non-GAAP gross margin, non-GAAP service gross margin, non-GAAP operating income (non-GAAP earnings from operations), non-GAAP operating margin, non-GAAP net profit (non-GAAP net earnings), non-GAAP diluted earnings per share in addition to the related GAAP measures provides investors with greater transparency to the information used by Bloom Energy management in its financial and operational decision making and allows investors to see Bloom Energy’s results “through the eyes” of management.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b5fc1fdcbe0bbf44\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.81875163\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Bloom Energy BE Q1 2026 earnings revenue fuel cell data center","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1557,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"240e2e7940356100\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy Q1 Revenue Doubling Validates Data Center Power Solution Growth Expectations; Shares Surge Over 16% Post-Market\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"240e2e7940356100\">>>","url":"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261834375-be-orcl-oracle-interest-stock-datacenter-nasdaq-tradingkey","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c79d445253b609f0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Bloom Energy Q1 Revenue Doubling Validates Data Center Power Solution Growth Expectations; Shares Surge Over 16% Post-Market. Bloom Energy reported Q1 2026 non-GAAP revenue of $751 million, up 130.4% year-over-year, beating expectations. The company raised full-year revenue guidance to $3.4 billion–$3.8 billion and expects gross margin around 34% by 2026. During the period, Bloom Energy's non-GAAP revenue reached $751 million, a significant year-over-year increase of 130.4%, surpassing the market expectation of $540 million. Regarding specific business segments, product revenue was recorded at $653 million, a 208.4% increase from $211.9 million in the same period last year and a slight 2.33% increase quarter-over-quarter; installation revenue was $25.931 million, down 22.94% year-over-year; service revenue reached $61.879 million, up 15.56% year-over-year; and electricity revenue was $9.896 million, a year-over-year decline of 63.28%. The most striking data point in this earnings report is the substantial growth in product revenue; this quarter, the company's product revenue surged 208.37% year-over-year to $653 million, accounting for 86.99% of total revenue.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c79d445253b609f0\">>>","score":0.9565735},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5ab4ffd797e251a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy Q1 Earnings Call Highlights\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5ab4ffd797e251a\">>>","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/bloom-energy-q1-earnings-call-003711170.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4481e29810c6baec\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n- Best gifts for sister-in-law. - Best gifts for mother-in-law. * Bloom delivered a “record” Q1 with **$751.1 million revenue (+130% YoY)**, expanded gross margin (31.5%), positive operating cash flow ($73.6M), and management raised full‑year 2026 revenue guidance to **$3.4–$3.8 billion** with upgraded profitability targets. * Demand from AI data centers is a major growth driver — Oracle’s Project Jupiter plans to replace turbines and diesel with **up to 2.45 GW** of Bloom Energy Servers, and Bloom says more than half of its current data‑center backlog comes from hyperscalers, neoclouds, and colocators building islanded microgrids. Bloom Energy (NYSE:BE) reported what founder, chairman, and CEO KR Sridhar called a “record first quarter,” with revenue, gross margin, and operating income coming in “materially above our prior outlook.” Management raised full-year 2026 guidance, citing accelerating demand for clean, reliable on-site power—particularly from AI data center customers—and confidence in Bloom’s ability to scale manufacturing capacity quickly.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4481e29810c6baec\">>>","score":0.94911116},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dfa9dd22c5650788\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy Soars Past $240 as AI Data Center Deals Fuel 130% Revenue Surge — BigGo Finance\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dfa9dd22c5650788\">>>","url":"https://finance.biggo.com/news/Yszb2Z0BNl__-4_GtS21","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"857efaa2b477f3b3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy reported first-quarter revenue of $751.1 million, a 130% year-over-year surge that crushed consensus estimates, and swung to a GAAP profit of $70.7 million from a year-ago loss. The company lifted its full-year 2026 revenue guidance to $3.4 billion to $3.8 billion, implying roughly 80% growth at the midpoint and placing the lower bound above the old upper bound. CEO KR Sridhar declared the company is rapidly becoming the standard for on-site data center power, noting that more than half of Bloom's data center backlog comes from customers other than Oracle. Bloom is rapidly becoming the standard and 'go-to choice' for on-site power.\" The statement landed with force because it arrived just one day after Oracle (ORCL) and BorderPlex Digital Assets confirmed that Project Jupiter—a multi-billion-dollar AI data center campus in New Mexico—will scrap previously planned gas turbines and diesel generators in favor of up to 2.45 gigawatts of Bloom's solid oxide fuel cell systems, making it one of the largest data center microgrids in the United States.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"857efaa2b477f3b3\">>>","score":0.94301796},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5bc211cd51e30b5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy Q1 2026 Earnings Call Revenue Up 130% As Data ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c5bc211cd51e30b5\">>>","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YEPJcscLVfA","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"473a6942e8454b17\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy Q1 2026 Earnings Call Revenue Up 130% As Data Center Demand Drives Record Product Sales · Comments.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"473a6942e8454b17\">>>","score":0.8934678},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3a33bedac5611ebb\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBloom Energy - Bloom Energy Reports Record First Quarter 2026 Results and Raises Full Year 2026 Guidance\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3a33bedac5611ebb\">>>","url":"https://investor.bloomenergy.com/press-releases/press-release-details/2026/Bloom-Energy-Reports-Record-First-Quarter-2026-Results-and-Raises-Full-Year-2026-Guidance/default.aspx","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b5fc1fdcbe0bbf44\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTo supplement Bloom Energy condensed consolidated financial statement information presented on a GAAP basis, Bloom Energy provides financial measures including non-GAAP gross profit, non-GAAP gross margin, non-GAAP operating income (non-GAAP earnings from operations), non-GAAP operating margin, non-GAAP net profit (non-GAAP net earnings), non-GAAP basic and diluted earnings per share and Adjusted EBITDA. Bloom Energy believes that providing financial measures including non-GAAP gross profit, non-GAAP gross margin, non-GAAP service gross margin, non-GAAP operating income (non-GAAP earnings from operations), non-GAAP operating margin, non-GAAP net profit (non-GAAP net earnings), non-GAAP diluted earnings per share in addition to the related GAAP measures provides investors with greater transparency to the information used by Bloom Energy management in its financial and operational decision making and allows investors to see Bloom Energy’s results “through the eyes” of management.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b5fc1fdcbe0bbf44\">>>","score":0.81875163}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387595107}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc526af2","parentId":"7c8a2301","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:15.108Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_4","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Vistra VST Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI data center power\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1547,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ac52d51afa64ea6d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVistra rises after reporting better-than-expected Q1 numbers - Sherwood News\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ac52d51afa64ea6d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://sherwood.news/markets/vistra-q1-earnings-report/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef55d46607f09f9a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPower provider Vistra, a key AI energy trade, reported better-than-expected results early Thursday, sending shares up in premarket trading. Adjusted EBITDA of $1.49 billion vs. expectations for $1.44 billion, per FactSet. Revenue of $5.6 billion vs. Vistra reaffirmed its 2026 Ongoing Operations Adjusted EBITDA guidance range of $6.8 billion to $7.6 billion and Ongoing Operations Adjusted Free Cash Flow before Growth range of $3.925 billion to $4.725 billion. The company’s Q1 sales were down about 10% year over year. For the quarter ended March 29, 2026, Krispy Kreme trimmed its net loss to **$22.8 million**, down from $33.3 million a year earlier, though still wider than the $10.8 million loss analysts had penciled in (compiled by Bloomberg). Adjusted EBITDA for Q1 came in at $33.1 million, a little more than the $30.6 million that analysts had been expecting. For full-year 2026, Peloton nudged up its revenue guidance to a range of $2.42 billion to $2.44 billion, and also boosted its adjusted EBITDA and free cash flow outlooks.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef55d46607f09f9a\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999722\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"064e6973aca5f1cf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSurging profit and new deals define Vistra Corp. (NYSE: VST) Q1 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"064e6973aca5f1cf\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/VST/10-q-vistra-corp-quarterly-earnings-report-9bf11d1ca3a5.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5901c645f1416aca\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nreported a strong turnaround for the quarter ended March 31, 2026.** Operating revenues rose to $5,640 million from $3,933 million a year earlier, and net income attributable to Vistra jumped to $1,029 million from a net loss of $268 million. In debt markets, Vistra Operations issued $2.25 billion of senior secured notes in January 2026 and, in April 2026, a further $4.0 billion of senior unsecured notes, using most proceeds to refinance higher-cost notes and repay the Term Loan B-3 facility. * **Sharp earnings turnaround and stronger cash generation**: Net income attributable to Vistra improved to $1,029 million from a $268 million loss, while cash provided by operating activities rose to $1,199 million from $599 million, supporting capital spending, dividends, and buybacks. * **Debt refinancing on longer-dated terms**: Vistra Operations issued $2.25 billion of senior secured notes in January 2026 and $4.0 billion of senior unsecured notes in April 2026, using about $3.968 billion to redeem 5.625% notes due 2027 and repay the Term Loan B-3 facility.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5901c645f1416aca\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99995935\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b82054250c878481\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCan Vistra's Data Center Power Contracts Finally Translate Into Quarterly Earnings That Match the Hype?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b82054250c878481\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.barchart.com/story/news/1755559/can-vistra-s-data-center-power-contracts-finally-translate-into-quarterly-earnings-that-match-the-hype\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0bd270af16ebc5bd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nreports first-quarter 2026 earnings before the open on Wednesday, May 7, with analysts expecting a dramatic turnaround from last year's loss to strong profitability. With the stock trading well below its 200-day moving average and technical signals flashing caution, the market is bracing for significant volatility around this closely watched release. The consensus estimate from 5 analysts calls for **earnings of $2.21 per share** on revenue of approximately $5.72 billion. The most recently reported quarter (Q4 2025) delivered **actual EPS of $2.18**, though that result missed the $2.51 consensus by 13.15%. Year-over-year, the Q1 2026 estimate represents a dramatic reversal: the company reported a **loss of $0.93 per share** in Q1 2025, meaning analysts expect a swing of more than $3 per share—a **+380.43% growth rate**—reflecting both easier comparisons and expectations for materially improved operations. However, the wide range of Q1 estimates—from a low of $1.07 to a high of $5.75—reflects significant uncertainty about near-term earnings power.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0bd270af16ebc5bd\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999528\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8ee2773f729aa1d2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVistra ( $VST) Q1 2026 Earnings Update Vistra reports Q1 2026 ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8ee2773f729aa1d2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://x.com/marketsday/status/2052370852524777806\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7830dba7f5f8db38\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVistra ( $VST) Q1 2026 Earnings Update ⚡ Vistra reports Q1 2026 revenue of $5.64 billion, rising 43% YoY Net Income comes in at $1.03\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7830dba7f5f8db38\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999398\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"958fc478cf5fa8a0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVistra Corp. (VST) Q1 Earnings and Revenues Top Estimates - May 8, 2026 - Zacks.com\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"958fc478cf5fa8a0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2917805/vistra-corp-vst-q1-earnings-and-revenues-top-estimates\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39d8077ba21372a9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWe use cookies to understand how you use our site and to improve your experience. By pressing \\\"Accept All\\\" or closing out of this banner, you consent to the use of all cookies and similar technologies and the sharing of information they collect with third parties. You can reject marketing cookies by pressing \\\"Deny Optional,\\\" but we still use essential, performance, and functional cookies. In addition, whether you \\\"Accept All,\\\" Deny Optional,\\\" click the X or otherwise continue to use the site, you accept our Privacy Policy and Terms of Service, revised from time to time. ### Most Viewed Stocks on Zacks.com. Based on total page views over the last 7 trading days. ### Trending Stocks on Zacks.com. Based on page view growth over the last 3 trading days. While the magnitude and direction of estimate revisions could change following the company's just-released earnings report, the current status translates into a Zacks Rank #3 (Hold) for the stock.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39d8077ba21372a9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99986863\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Vistra VST Q1 2026 earnings revenue AI data center power","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1547,"externalContent":{"untruste