{"type":"message","id":"7465f41f","parentId":"fc526af2","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:15.109Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bxl3sotaxkl5_5","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"TSMC TSM Q1 2026 earnings revenue advanced packaging CoWoS\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1620,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6bdda378e845ed0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC Reports First Quarter EPS of NT$22.08\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a6bdda378e845ed0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://investor.tsmc.com/english/encrypt/files/encrypt_file/reports/2026-04/e85216eea8dccd8ca75d7e040e8d57be3ccd618b/1Q26%20EarningsRelease.pdf\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dac5bfee42752606\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nApril 16, 2026 TSMC Page 1 of 2 Hsinchu, Taiwan, R.O.C., April 16, 2026 -- TSMC today announced consolidated revenue of NT$1,134.10 billion, net income of NT$572.48 billion, and diluted earnings per share of NT$22.08 (US$3.49 per ADR unit) for the first quarter ended March 31, 2026. “Moving into second quarter 2026, we expect our business to be supported by continued strong demand for our leading-edge process technologies.” Based on the Company’s current business outlook, management expects the overall performance for second quarter 2026 to be as follows: • Revenue is expected to be between US$39.0 billion and US$40.2 billion; And, based on the exchange rate assumption of 1 US dollar to 31.7 NT dollars, • Gross profit margin is expected to be between 65.5% and 67.5%; • Operating profit margin is expected to be between 56.5% and 58.5%.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dac5bfee42752606\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.92620385\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a08fa552b3fad9b3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC posts Q1 revenue surge of 40.6% YoY\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a08fa552b3fad9b3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.manufacturingdive.com/news/tsmc-q1-2026-revenue-q2-guidance-ai-arizona/817728/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7059be7263e7f43d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC reported Q1 2026 revenue of $35.6B, up 6.4% over Q4 2025. ... advanced packaging fab. In March of last year, TSMC announced plans\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7059be7263e7f43d\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.92392945\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"93555186d092287d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTaiwan Semiconductor Manufactur (TSM) Q1 FY2026 earnings call transcript\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"93555186d092287d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/TSM/earnings/TSM-Q1-2026-earnings_call-541404.html/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c60ec7c41e47c09f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n## Earnings call TSMC delivered Q1 2026 revenue of $35.9B (up 6.4% QoQ, 8.4% in TWD), beating guidance, with gross margin rising to 66.2% and operating margin to 58.1%. TSMC delivered Q1 2026 revenue of $35.9B (up 6.4% QoQ, 8.4% in TWD), beating guidance, with gross margin rising to 66.2% and operating margin to 58.1%. First, TSMC's Senior Vice President and CFO, Mr. Wendell Huang, will summarize our operations in the first quarter 2026, followed by our guidance for the second quarter 2026. Now, I would like to turn the call over to TSMC CFO, Mr. Wendell Huang, for the summary of operations and the current quarter guidance. After that, I will provide the guidance for the second quarter 2026. As we have said before, the initial ramp-up of our 2 nm technology will start to dilute our gross margin in the second half of this year, and we expect between 2% and 3% dilution for the full year of 2026.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c60ec7c41e47c09f\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9220975\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f0469a66a1aab6d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC Q1 revenue tops $35.9bn on strong 3nm demand ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f0469a66a1aab6d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.eenewseurope.com/en/tsmc-q1-revenue-tops-35-9bn-on-strong-3nm-demand/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0778b1e23277e555\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC reported strong first-quarter 2026 financial results, with revenue and profit climbing sharply on continued demand for advanced process nodes. The world’s largest contract chipmaker posted consolidated revenue of NT$1.134 trillion and net income of NT$572.48 billion for the quarter ended March 31. For engineers, semiconductor companies and supply-chain players following manufacturing trends, the results highlight the accelerating demand for leading-edge nodes such as 3nm and 5nm — technologies that underpin AI, high-performance computing and next-generation electronics. “Our business in the first quarter was supported by strong demand for our leading-edge process technologies,” said Huang. “Moving into second quarter 2026, we expect our business to be supported by continued strong demand for our leading-edge process technologies.”. Looking ahead to the second quarter of 2026, TSMC expects revenue to reach between $39.0 billion and $40.2 billion. The outlook suggests that demand for cutting-edge manufacturing — driven by AI and high-performance computing — continues to shape the semiconductor industry’s growth trajectory in 2026.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0778b1e23277e555\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9123193\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5ca172d767443b7e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTSMC 2026 Q1 Quarterly Results - Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5ca172d767443b7e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2026/q1\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f93f8c273546b107\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*   [](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2026/q1#). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/technology). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing). *   [GIGAFAB® Facilities](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing/gigafab). *   [Agile and Intelligent Operations](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing/intelligent_operations). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/oip). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/services). *   [CyberShuttle®](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/services/cyberShuttle). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/grandAlliance). *   [Investors](https://investor.tsmc.com/english). [Investors](https://investor.tsmc.com/english). *   [Overview](https://investor.tsmc.com/english). *   [Credit Rating](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/credit-rating). *   [About TSMC](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). *   [About TSMC](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). [About TSMC](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC/company_profile). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/technology). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing). *   [GIGAFAB® Facilities](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing/gigafab). *   [Agile and Intelligent Operations](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/manufacturing/intelligent_operations). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/oip). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/services). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/dedicatedFoundry/grandAlliance). *   [Overview](https://investor.tsmc.com/english). *   [Credit Rating](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/credit-rating). *   [About TSMC](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC). *   [Overview](https://www.tsmc.com/english/aboutTSMC/company_profile). 1.   [Home](https://www.tsmc.com/english). 2.   [Investors](https://investor.tsmc.com/english). [](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2026/q1). *   [2026](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results). *   [2025](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2025/q4). *   [2024](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2024/q4). *   [2023](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2023/q4). *   [2022](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2022/q4). *   [2021](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2021/q4). *   [2020](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2020/q4). *   [2019](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2019/q4). *   [2018](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2018/q4). *   [2017](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2017/q4). *   [2016](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2016/q4). *   [2015](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2015/q4). *   [2014](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2014/q4). *   [2013](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2013/q4). *   [2012](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2012/q4). *   [2011](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2011/q4). *   [2010](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly-results/2010/q4). *   [2009](https://investor.tsmc.com/english/quarterly