{"type":"compaction","id":"d1468da5","parentId":"7465f41f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:33:56.919Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\nContinue analyzing 21 unanalyzed financial reports (財報季報) for Q2 2026, building on existing AI industry trend analysis framework.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Uses the \"七層蛋糕\" (seven-layer cake) AI industry architecture framework for classification\n- Focus on Q2 2026 AI industry trends\n- Prior analysis already completed for some companies\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Completed Q2 2026 AI industry trend analysis covering:\n  - Price increase dynamics (GPU, CPU, DRAM, PCB, optical components)\n  - Five-layer to seven-layer architecture evolution\n  - Energy/power infrastructure as compute ceiling\n  - Momentum chasing patterns (Q2 leaders: SNDK/MU, VRT)\n  - Risk factors (NVIDIA earnings, inventory levels, P/E ratios)\n- [x] Categorized companies across 7 sectors with ticker symbols\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Analyzing remaining 21 unanalyzed financial reports/quarterly reports\n\n### Blocked\n- (none specified)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Framework**: Industry analysis uses \"七層蛋糕\" model: Energy → Silicon → Memory → Networking → Systems → Models → Agents\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Identify which 21 specific companies/reports need analysis\n2. Analyze financial reports within the 7-layer framework context\n3. Cross-reference Q2 earnings with previously identified trend themes (price hikes, power constraints, margin expansion)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Energy & Power**: CEG, BE, VST, NEE\n- **Compute Silicon**: NVDA, AMD, INTC, ARM\n- **Memory & Storage**: MU, WDC, STX, 000660.KS\n- **Networking**: AVGO, MRVL, ANET\n- **Systems & Cooling**: VRT, SMCI, ETN, 2317.TW\n- **Models & MLOps**: MSFT, META, GOOGL\n- **Agents & Apps**: PLTR, CRWD, NOW\n- Previous Q2 analysis highlights memory (SNDK/MU) and liquid cooling (VRT) as margin expansion leaders\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nJo asked for analysis of 21 stocks not yet analyzed from a 7-layer AI infrastructure framework. The list spans energy/power (CEG, BE, VST, NEE), compute silicon (NVDA, AMD, INTC, ARM), memory (MU, WDC, STX, SK Hynix), networking (AVGO, MRVL, ANET), systems/cooling (SMCI, ETN, Foxconn), models/MLOps (MSFT, META, GOOGL), and agentic AI (CRWD, NOW). VRT and PLTR were confirmed already analyzed.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Confirmed VRT and PLTR already analyzed in current session via session history review\n- Conducted multiple batched web searches gathering Q1 2026 earnings data for most major names\n- Data collected: NVDA ($0.81 EPS, $44.06B revenue +69%), AMD ($10.25B revenue +38%), MU (record $23.9B), CEG (May 11 earnings, EPS $2.61 guide), AVGO ($19.3B +29%, AI $10.7B), MSFT ($82.9B +18%, Azure +39-40%), META ($55.02B ad revenue +33%, capex $145B), MRVL (AI majority of data center), ANET ($2.71B +35.1%, raised outlook), ETN ($7.5B +17%)\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe retained suffix continues with additional web searches for remaining stocks (SMCI, GOOGL, CRWD, NOW, INTC, ARM, WDC, STX, BE, VST, NEE) and organizing the compiled data into structured analysis by the 7-layer framework categories for output to Jo.\n\n<read-files>\nC:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\dfe6ed1a-aff7-4e6d-ba00-7263a0af322b.jsonl\nC:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\e98119d9-943b-4f3f-a322-efcfdbeeece6.jsonl.reset.2026-05-10T04-29-41.919Z\nC:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\e98119d9-943b-4f3f-a322-efcfdbeeece6.trajectory.jsonl\n</read-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"8b9317a5","tokensBefore":88662,"details":{"readFiles":["C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\dfe6ed1a-aff7-4e6d-ba00-7263a0af322b.jsonl","C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\e98119d9-943b-4f3f-a322-efcfdbeeece6.jsonl.reset.2026-05-10T04-29-41.919Z","C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\sessions\\e98119d9-943b-4f3f-a322-efcfdbeeece6.trajectory.jsonl"],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
