{"type":"message","id":"e5dc35db","parentId":"0fd96bc2","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:34:05.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me search for the remaining stocks: NEE, ARM, and 000660.KS (SK Hynix).\n","thinkingSignature":"a6f560dafb5fe62fe1bc87e477ccab17e0e151c7f86c6f9644d79ccdea43b65d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"NextEra Energy NEE Q1 2026 earnings revenue Florida Power Light data center"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"ARM Holdings ARM Q1 2026 earnings revenue royalty AI chips"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_3","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"SK Hynix 000660 KS Q1 2026 earnings revenue HBM AI memory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36815,"output":168,"cacheRead":608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37591,"cost":{"input":0.011044499999999999,"output":0.0002016,"cacheRead":0.000036479999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011282579999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778387638233,"responseId":"064f3dba54998eaa48d8037a9b931364"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c96a13a4","parentId":"e5dc35db","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:34:08.395Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"NextEra Energy NEE Q1 2026 earnings revenue Florida Power Light data center\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1669,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"00eccd5ab094eda8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[PDF] NextEra Energy reports first-quarter 2026 financial results\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"00eccd5ab094eda8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.investor.nexteraenergy.com/~/media/Files/N/NEE-IR/reports-and-fillings/quarterly-earnings/2026/Q1%202026/2026-0423%20NEEQ12026News%20Release%20vF.pdf\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"66ae0d59fcc91ca1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n(NYSE: NEE) today reported 2026 first-quarter net income attributable to NextEra Energy on a GAAP basis of $2.182 billion, or $1.04 per share, compared to $833 million, or $0.40 per share, for the first quarter of 2025. On an adjusted basis, NextEra Energy's 2026 first-quarter earnings were $2.275 billion, or $1.09 per share, compared to $2.038 billion, or $0.99 per share, in the first quarter of 2025. Importantly, our forecasted growth is visible and balanced between our regulated and long-term contracted businesses, and we expect to grow adjusted earnings per share at a compound annual growth rate of 8%+ through 2032 and are targeting the same from 2032 through 2035, all off the 2025 base.\\\" FPL FPL reported first-quarter 2026 net income of $1.462 billion, or $0.70 per share, compared to $1.316 billion, or $0.64 per share, for the prior-year comparable quarter.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"66ae0d59fcc91ca1\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9222657\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6388c35e19a9cb1d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNextEra Energy, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap | AllInvestView\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6388c35e19a9cb1d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.allinvestview.com/earnings/NEE/q1-2026/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2afe2e21e7592e5f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# NextEra Energy, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap. NEE Q1 2026  April 23, 2026. NextEra Energy delivered a solid start to 2026, with adjusted EPS up 10% year-over-year driven by robust operational performance at FPL and Energy Resources, supporting strong growth prospects. * FPL added nearly 100,000 customers in Q1 and plans to invest $90-100 billion through 2032, supporting Florida’s projected 4.7% annual GDP growth to 2040. * FPL’s 10-year plan includes 4 GW of gas, over 12 GW of solar, and 7 GW of storage, maintaining low-cost, reliable service amid continued infrastructure expansion. For the complete transcript and financial data, visit NEE on AllInvestView. AAL · Q1 2026  Alaska Air Group, Inc. ALK · Q1 2026  American Express Company. AXP · Q1 2026  Banc of California, Inc. BANC · Q1 2026  Bankinter, S.A. BKT.MC · Q1 2026  Blackstone Inc. BX · Q1 2026  CBRE Group, Inc. CBRE · Q1 2026  Crown Castle International Corp. Track NextEra Energy, Inc. in your portfolio with real-time analytics, dividend tracking, and more.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2afe2e21e7592e5f\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9125066\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39abb45b237ea01f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNextEra Energy adds record 4 GW of renewables and storage backlog in Q1 – pv magazine USA\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39abb45b237ea01f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://pv-magazine-usa.com/2026/04/23/nextera-energy-adds-record-4-gw-of-renewables-and-storage-backlog-in-q1/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"594eab962ada76a4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# NextEra Energy adds record 4 GW of renewables and storage backlog in Q1. The Florida-based utility and energy infrastructure giant posted a 10% year-over-year increase in adjusted earnings, supported by a massive quarter for project origination and continued solar expansion in its regulated utility segment. NextEra Energy reported first-quarter 2026 GAAP net income of $2.182 billion, or $1.04 per share, compared to $833 million, or $0.40 per share, in the same period last year. The company’s competitive energy subsidiary, NextEra Energy Resources, set a new company record for renewables and storage origination by adding 4 GW to its backlog. The Energy Resources subsidiary reported adjusted earnings of $1.038 billion for the quarter, a significant climb from the $908 million reported in the first quarter of 2025. The company expects to grow adjusted earnings per share at a compound annual growth rate of 8% or more through 2032 and is targeting the same growth rate from 2032 through 2035.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"594eab962ada76a4\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.86108357\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6139f65b11b603c2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEarnings call transcript: NextEra Energy Q1 2026 results beat EPS ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6139f65b11b603c2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-nextera-energy-q1-2026-results-beat-eps-forecast-93CH-4633221\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"aae005b8920639f8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHowever, the revenue of $6.7 billion fell short of the anticipated $7.29 billion, marking an 8.09% miss. This mixed result highlights the\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"aae005b8920639f8\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.767429\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"275699e7f56f9266\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNextEra Energy soars to all-time high as Q1 profit more than doubled\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"275699e7f56f9266\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/topstocks/nextera-energy-soars-to-all-time-high-as-q1-profit-more-than-doubled/ar-AA21zgW2\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a162d256d37b9ef5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNextEra's (NEE) regulated utility, Florida Power & Light, posted Q1 net income of $1.46B, or $0.70/share, up 11.1% Y/Y, lifted by an increase in customers\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a162d256d37b9ef5\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.7596005\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"NextEra Energy NEE Q1 2026 earnings revenue Florida Power Light data center","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1669,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"00eccd5ab094eda8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[PDF] NextEra Energy reports first-quarter 2026 financial results\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"00eccd5ab094eda8\">>>","url":"https://www.investor.nexteraenergy.com/~/media/Files/N/NEE-IR/reports-and-fillings/quarterly-earnings/2026/Q1%202026/2026-0423%20NEEQ12026News%20Release%20vF.pdf","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"66ae0d59fcc91ca1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n(NYSE: NEE) today reported 2026 first-quarter net income attributable to NextEra Energy on a GAAP basis of $2.182 billion, or $1.04 per share, compared to $833 million, or $0.40 per share, for the first quarter of 2025. On an adjusted basis, NextEra Energy's 2026 first-quarter earnings were $2.275 billion, or $1.09 per share, compared to $2.038 billion, or $0.99 per share, in the first quarter of 2025. Importantly, our forecasted growth is visible and balanced between our regulated and long-term contracted businesses, and we expect to grow adjusted earnings per share at a compound annual growth rate of 8%+ through 2032 and are targeting the same from 2032 through 2035, all off the 2025 base.\" FPL FPL reported first-quarter 2026 net income of $1.462 billion, or $0.70 per share, compared to $1.316 billion, or $0.64 per share, for the prior-year comparable quarter.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"66ae0d59fcc91ca1\">>>","score":0.9222657},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6388c35e19a9cb1d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nNextEra Energy, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap | AllInvestView\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6388c35e19a9cb1d\">>>","url":"https://www.allinvestview.com/earnings/NEE/q1-2026/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2afe2e21e7592e5f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# NextEra Energy, Inc. Q1 2026 Earnings Recap. NEE Q1 2026  April 23, 2026. NextEra Energy delivered a solid start to 2026, with adjusted EPS up 10% year-over-year driven by robust operational performance at FPL and Energy Resources, supporting strong growth prospects. * FPL added nearly 100,000 customers in Q1 and plans to invest $90-100 billion through 2032, supporting Florida’s projected 4.7% annual GDP growth to 2040. * FPL’s 10-year plan includes 4 GW of gas, over 12 GW of solar, and 7 GW of storage, maintaining low-cost, reliable service amid continued infrastructure expansion. For the complete transcript and financial data, visit NEE on AllInvestView. AAL · Q1 2026  Alaska Air Group, Inc. ALK · Q1 2026  American Express Company. AXP · Q1 2026  Banc of California, Inc. BANC · Q1 2026  Bankinter, S.A. BKT.MC · Q1 2026  Blackstone Inc. BX · Q1 2026  CBRE Group, Inc. CBRE · Q1 2026  Crown Castle International Corp. Track NextEra Energy, Inc. in your portfolio with real-time analytics, dividend tracking, and more.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2afe2e21e7592e5f\">>>","score":0.9125066},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39abb45b237ea01f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nNextEra Energy adds record 4 GW of renewables and storage backlog in Q1 – pv magazine USA\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39abb45b237ea01f\">>>","url":"https://pv-magazine-usa.com/2026/04/23/nextera-energy-adds-record-4-gw-of-renewables-and-storage-backlog-in-q1/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"594eab962ada76a4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# NextEra Energy adds record 4 GW of renewables and storage backlog in Q1. The Florida-based utility and energy infrastructure giant posted a 10% year-over-year increase in adjusted earnings, supported by a massive quarter for project origination and continued solar expansion in its regulated utility segment. NextEra Energy reported first-quarter 2026 GAAP net income of $2.182 billion, or $1.04 per share, compared to $833 million, or $0.40 per share, in the same period last year. The company’s competitive energy subsidiary, NextEra Energy Resources, set a new company record for renewables and storage origination by adding 4 GW to its backlog. The Energy Resources subsidiary reported adjusted earnings of $1.038 billion for the quarter, a significant climb from the $908 million reported in the first quarter of 2025. The company expects to grow adjusted earnings per share at a compound annual growth rate of 8% or more through 2032 and is targeting the same growth rate from 2032 through 2035.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"594eab962ada76a4\">>>","score":0.86108357},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6139f65b11b603c2\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEarnings call transcript: NextEra Energy Q1 2026 results beat EPS ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6139f65b11b603c2\">>>","url":"https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-nextera-energy-q1-2026-results-beat-eps-forecast-93CH-4633221","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"aae005b8920639f8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHowever, the revenue of $6.7 billion fell short of the anticipated $7.29 billion, marking an 8.09% miss. This mixed result highlights the\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"aae005b8920639f8\">>>","score":0.767429},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"275699e7f56f9266\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nNextEra Energy soars to all-time high as Q1 profit more than doubled\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"275699e7f56f9266\">>>","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-us/money/topstocks/nextera-energy-soars-to-all-time-high-as-q1-profit-more-than-doubled/ar-AA21zgW2","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a162d256d37b9ef5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nNextEra's (NEE) regulated utility, Florida Power & Light, posted Q1 net income of $1.46B, or $0.70/share, up 11.1% Y/Y, lifted by an increase in customers\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a162d256d37b9ef5\">>>","score":0.7596005}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387648395}}
{"type":"message","id":"bc990396","parentId":"c96a13a4","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:34:08.396Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"ARM Holdings ARM Q1 2026 earnings revenue royalty AI chips\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1792,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5624226e7fe5e16e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nARM Holdings PLC (ARM) Q1 2026 Earnings Call Highlights: Strong Revenue Growth and AI Momentum\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5624226e7fe5e16e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q1-073711816.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dd5a6e52865c61f9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n- Best gifts for sister-in-law. - Best birthday gifts for her. - Best gifts for mother-in-law. - Best anniversary gifts for wife. - Best streaming device of 2026. # ARM Holdings PLC (ARM) Q1 2026 Earnings Call Highlights: Strong Revenue Growth and AI Momentum. * **Royalty Revenue:** $585 million, up 25% year-on-year. * **Non-GAAP EPS:** $0.35, above the midpoint of guidance range. * **Q2 Non-GAAP EPS Guidance:** Range of $0.29 to $0.37. * ARM Holdings PLC (NASDAQ:ARM) reported its second highest revenue quarter at $1.05 billion, with royalty revenue reaching $585 million, up 25% year-on-year. * The company is experiencing strong momentum in AI, with over 22 million developers building on ARM, representing more than 80% of the global base. * Licensing revenue decreased by 1% year-on-year, following a strong previous quarter. **A**: Rene Haas, CEO: We are exploring further integration due to the complexity of chips and the demand for better starting points in SOC development.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dd5a6e52865c61f9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9718032\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c446c6259714d3cc\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArm Holdings Rides AI Wave With Record Earnings - The Globe and Mail\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c446c6259714d3cc\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/markets/stocks/ARM/pressreleases/1821508/arm-holdings-rides-ai-wave-with-record-earnings/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39dbdd1d2ae1192e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArm Holdings’ latest earnings call struck an upbeat tone, as management highlighted record revenue, earnings and margins alongside accelerating demand for its AGI CPUs and growing data center traction. For the full fiscal 2026, revenue climbed 23% to $4.92 billion, underscoring robust demand across licensing and royalties and reinforcing Arm’s transition from a mobile‑centric IP vendor to a diversified computing powerhouse. License and other revenue surged 29% year over year to $819 million in Q4, while royalty revenue rose 11% to $671 million, despite some mobile softness. For the first quarter of fiscal 2027, Arm guided revenue to $1.26 billion plus or minus $50 million, implying around 20% year‑over‑year growth at the midpoint. The company reaffirmed longer‑term goals of $15 billion in AGI CPU revenue and $10 billion in IP revenue by fiscal 2031, implying more than $9 of EPS as license revenue skews to the back half of the year and royalty growth stays near 20%.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39dbdd1d2ae1192e\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9338243\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c8171edf3fcbcaf9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArm (ARM) Q1 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c8171edf3fcbcaf9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q1-2026_FGFOjCBI\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ecfa866b47958338\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*   [![Image 5: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Q3 2026 4 Feb 2026 Q3 revenue up 26% YoY, driven by Armv9, AI, and data center growth; margins remain strong.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q3-2026_FGFOfM3b). *   [![Image 6: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Q1 2025 2 Feb 2026 Revenue up 39% to $939m, led by Armv9, AI, and licensing, with robust outlook ahead.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q1-2025_FGFOjT6g). *   [![Image 7: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Q2 2025 16 Jan 2026 Q2 revenue hit $844M, up 5%, with 23% royalty growth and strong Armv9 adoption.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q2-2025_FGFOjJwe). *   [![Image 8: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Q3 2025 9 Jan 2026 Revenue up 19% to $983M, strong royalty growth, and raised FY2025 guidance.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q3-2025_FGFOjD3c). *   [![Image 9: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Q2 2026 10 Dec 2025 Revenue up 34%, net income more than doubled, driven by strong licensing and royalty growth.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-q2-2026_FGFOfee2). *   [![Image 10: Logotype for Arm](https://assets.quartr.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.quartr.com%2Fcompany-logos%2F93777-2023-09-11-11-13-55.png&w=64&q=100) ARM Investor Update 2 Dec 2025 AI-driven growth, R&D investment, and ecosystem expansion fuel rising revenue and market share.](https://quartr.com/events/arm-holdings-plc-arm-investor-update_FGFOjfzt).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ecfa866b47958338\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.91490877\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ea3afba6dedbb56d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[PDF] Shareholder Letter - Arm Investor Relations\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ea3afba6dedbb56d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://investors.arm.com/static-files/344cbcfe-e28b-48ab-b272-c856e0756a91\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"687cf2a96002c830\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRoyalty revenue was $2.61 billion, up 21%, and licensing revenue was $2.31 billion, up 25%. Non-GAAP EPS was also a record at $1.77. Fiscal 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"687cf2a96002c830\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9123193\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"083e0036667572b5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArm forecasts higher-than-expected revenue on surging AI data center demand\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"083e0036667572b5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reuters.com/business/arm-forecasts-upbeat-revenue-surging-ai-data-center-demand-2026-05-06/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4d10a8eb301ae7d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Skip to main content](https://www.reuters.com/business/arm-forecasts-upbeat-revenue-surging-ai-data-center-demand-2026-05-06/#main-content). *   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). ## [Browse World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). ## [Browse Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Take Five](https://www.reuters.com/business/take-five/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). ## [Browse Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). May 6 (Reuters) - Arm Holdings [(O9Ty.F), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/O9Ty.F), forecast first-quarter revenue above Wall ​Street expectations on Wednesday, benefiting from higher adoption of its chip technology as tech companies spend heavily on artificial ‌intelligence compute. ## [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). *   [Media Center, opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/media-center/). *   [](https://www.facebook.com/Reuters). *   [](https://www.instagram.com/Reuters). By continuing to use our services, you acknowledge this use of cookies and other tracking technologies, which may include storing and accessing information on your device and processing your browsing data.You can opt out of any Sharing or Sale of your personal information, as well as any Profiling or Targeted Advertising, and manage the above activities for this website at any time by clicking the [Manage Cookies & Your Privacy Choices](https://www.reuters.com/business/arm-forecasts-upbeat-revenue-surging-ai-data-center-demand-2026-05-06/) link here or the equivalent link in our footer. [Close](https://www.reuters.com/business/arm-forecasts-upbeat-revenue-surging-ai-data-center-demand-2026-05-06/).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4d10a8eb301ae7d\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.74273956\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["query","provider","count","tookMs","externalContent","results"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387648395}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0d6a95d","parentId":"bc990396","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:34:08.396Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2iqm5c24j5s5_3","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"SK Hynix 000660 KS Q1 2026 earnings revenue HBM AI memory\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1750,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b935419389eeec6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDaily Brief Equity Bottom-Up: SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits and more | Smartkarma\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b935419389eeec6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.smartkarma.com/home/daily-briefs/daily-brief-equity-bottom-up-sk-hyn…more/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"92a13bacb5eec013\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Daily Brief Equity Bottom-Up: SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits and more. * SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits. * SK Hynix: Record Results in 1Q 2026. * HYNIX is a key benefactor from the AI theme, but its valuations remain the cheapest in the AI ecosystem despite having one of the best ROE and FCF yields. * ASMPT Q126 revenue was up 32% YoY to HK$3.97 billion (US$508 million). * The Group’s Photonics solutions achieved a five-fold increase in YoY revenue growth, propelled by strong demand from high-speed transceivers of 800G and beyond. * SK Hynix (000660 KS) reported slightly better than expected sales and operating profit in 1Q 2026. * Post 1Q 2026 results, I do not expect the consensus to make material changes to SK Hynix’s sales and operating profit estimates in the next two years.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"92a13bacb5eec013\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999907\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"208c0338a1be1ebd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSK Hynix Shares Surge Following Historic Q1 Earnings Powered by AI Chip Sales | MEXC News\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"208c0338a1be1ebd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.mexc.com/news/1048170\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c39aba47e44accf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSK Hynix achieves record Q1 net profit of $27.2B, up 400% YoY, with 72% operating margin driven by surging AI memory demand and HBM market dominance. The post SKSK Hynix achieves record Q1 net profit of $27.2B, up 400% YoY, with 72% operating margin driven by surging AI memory demand and HBM market dominance. # SK Hynix Shares Surge Following Historic Q1 Earnings Powered by AI Chip Sales. For feedback or concerns regarding this content, please contact us at crypto.news@mexc.com. * First-quarter net profit reached a record 40.3 trillion won ($27.2B), representing a nearly 400% increase compared to the same period last year. * SK Hynix commands a dominant 57% share of the high-bandwidth memory market and expects to introduce HBM4E samples in the latter half of 2026. * A massive 19 trillion won investment in a new South Korean manufacturing facility is underway to address surging AI-related demand. The company’s operating margin climbed to an all-time high of 72%.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c39aba47e44accf\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99998844\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09173de39620f0d8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSK Hynix Q1 2026 Earnings: A Historic AI Explosion (Seasonality is ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09173de39620f0d8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sDfiH6u-Yq0\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fbed12e3eb4f4188\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*Historic Financials:* Revenue tripled to 52.6 trillion KRW (up 198% YoY), while operating profit exploded by roughly 5x to 37.6 trillion KRW,\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fbed12e3eb4f4188\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99997723\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"853154e890caf853\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMLQ.ai | AI for investors\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"853154e890caf853\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mlq.ai/news/sk-hyn…ices/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"972937bf4a9f879e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n* SK Hynix reported Q1 operating profit of 37.6 trillion won, up more than five-fold year-over-year. * Operating margin hit 72%, driven by 83% quarter-over-quarter rise in DRAM contract prices and AI demand for HBM. SK Hynix announced first-quarter results showing operating profit of 37.6 trillion won, a more than five-fold increase from the prior year, with revenue climbing 198% to 52.6 trillion won on strong AI-driven demand for high-bandwidth memory and rising DRAM prices.[1][2]. The profit figure surpassed analyst estimates ranging from 32.69 trillion to 40.3 trillion won.[2][7] Revenue growth reflected a super cycle in the memory market, with DRAM contract prices rising 90-95% and NAND flash prices up 55-60% quarter-over-quarter according to TrendForce data.[1]. The 72% operating margin underscores pricing power in a market where DRAM and NAND saw 90-95% and 55-60% increases, respectively, outpacing prior forecasts.[1][4] This performance positions SK Hynix ahead of competitors, as its focus on advanced nodes has captured a larger share of high-margin AI memory sales compared to traditional DRAM segments.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"972937bf4a9f879e\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99994695\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ca88f1b256d84564\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n37.61 trillion won ($25.4 billion), up 405% YoY and 96% QoQ, with ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ca88f1b256d84564\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://x.com/marketsday/status/2047099485277626721\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5ec3775a6e4412fa\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSK Hynix reported its strongest-ever quarterly results, driven by surging AI demand for high-bandwidth memory (HBM) and broader memory chips.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5ec3775a6e4412fa\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99992275\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"SK Hynix 000660 KS Q1 2026 earnings revenue HBM AI memory","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1750,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9b935419389eeec6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDaily Brief Equity Bottom-Up: SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits and more | Smartkarma\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9b935419389eeec6\">>>","url":"https://www.smartkarma.com/home/daily-briefs/daily-brief-equity-bottom-up-sk-hynix-000660-ks-1q26-results-ai-driving-out-of-this-world-profits-and-more/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"92a13bacb5eec013\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# Daily Brief Equity Bottom-Up: SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits and more. * SK Hynix (000660 KS) 1Q26 Results: AI Driving Out of This World Profits. * SK Hynix: Record Results in 1Q 2026. * HYNIX is a key benefactor from the AI theme, but its valuations remain the cheapest in the AI ecosystem despite having one of the best ROE and FCF yields. * ASMPT Q126 revenue was up 32% YoY to HK$3.97 billion (US$508 million). * The Group’s Photonics solutions achieved a five-fold increase in YoY revenue growth, propelled by strong demand from high-speed transceivers of 800G and beyond. * SK Hynix (000660 KS) reported slightly better than expected sales and operating profit in 1Q 2026. * Post 1Q 2026 results, I do not expect the consensus to make material changes to SK Hynix’s sales and operating profit estimates in the next two years.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"92a13bacb5eec013\">>>","score":0.9999907},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"208c0338a1be1ebd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSK Hynix Shares Surge Following Historic Q1 Earnings Powered by AI Chip Sales | MEXC News\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"208c0338a1be1ebd\">>>","url":"https://www.mexc.com/news/1048170","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9c39aba47e44accf\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSK Hynix achieves record Q1 net profit of $27.2B, up 400% YoY, with 72% operating margin driven by surging AI memory demand and HBM market dominance. The post SKSK Hynix achieves record Q1 net profit of $27.2B, up 400% YoY, with 72% operating margin driven by surging AI memory demand and HBM market dominance. # SK Hynix Shares Surge Following Historic Q1 Earnings Powered by AI Chip Sales. For feedback or concerns regarding this content, please contact us at crypto.news@mexc.com. * First-quarter net profit reached a record 40.3 trillion won ($27.2B), representing a nearly 400% increase compared to the same period last year. * SK Hynix commands a dominant 57% share of the high-bandwidth memory market and expects to introduce HBM4E samples in the latter half of 2026. * A massive 19 trillion won investment in a new South Korean manufacturing facility is underway to address surging AI-related demand. The company’s operating margin climbed to an all-time high of 72%.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9c39aba47e44accf\">>>","score":0.99998844},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09173de39620f0d8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSK Hynix Q1 2026 Earnings: A Historic AI Explosion (Seasonality is ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09173de39620f0d8\">>>","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sDfiH6u-Yq0","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fbed12e3eb4f4188\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n*Historic Financials:* Revenue tripled to 52.6 trillion KRW (up 198% YoY), while operating profit exploded by roughly 5x to 37.6 trillion KRW,\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fbed12e3eb4f4188\">>>","score":0.99997723},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"853154e890caf853\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMLQ.ai | AI for investors\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"853154e890caf853\">>>","url":"https://mlq.ai/news/sk-hynix-reports-record-breaking-q1-profit-driven-by-surging-memory-chip-prices/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"972937bf4a9f879e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n* SK Hynix reported Q1 operating profit of 37.6 trillion won, up more than five-fold year-over-year. * Operating margin hit 72%, driven by 83% quarter-over-quarter rise in DRAM contract prices and AI demand for HBM. SK Hynix announced first-quarter results showing operating profit of 37.6 trillion won, a more than five-fold increase from the prior year, with revenue climbing 198% to 52.6 trillion won on strong AI-driven demand for high-bandwidth memory and rising DRAM prices.[1][2]. The profit figure surpassed analyst estimates ranging from 32.69 trillion to 40.3 trillion won.[2][7] Revenue growth reflected a super cycle in the memory market, with DRAM contract prices rising 90-95% and NAND flash prices up 55-60% quarter-over-quarter according to TrendForce data.[1]. The 72% operating margin underscores pricing power in a market where DRAM and NAND saw 90-95% and 55-60% increases, respectively, outpacing prior forecasts.[1][4] This performance positions SK Hynix ahead of competitors, as its focus on advanced nodes has captured a larger share of high-margin AI memory sales compared to traditional DRAM segments.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"972937bf4a9f879e\">>>","score":0.99994695},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ca88f1b256d84564\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n37.61 trillion won ($25.4 billion), up 405% YoY and 96% QoQ, with ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ca88f1b256d84564\">>>","url":"https://x.com/marketsday/status/2047099485277626721","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5ec3775a6e4412fa\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSK Hynix reported its strongest-ever quarterly results, driven by surging AI demand for high-bandwidth memory (HBM) and broader memory chips.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5ec3775a6e4412fa\">>>","score":0.99992275}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778387648395}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce4e285b","parentId":"c0d6a95d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T04:36:35.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough data to compile the full analysis. Let me organize everything by the 七層蛋糕 framework.\n\nLet me compile all the Q2/Q1 2026 earnings data:\n\n**第一層 - 能源與電力基建 (Energy & Power)**\n- CEG: May 11 earnings, EPS $2.61 guide (from earlier summary)\n- BE: Q1 2026 Revenue $751M (+130% YoY), raised full-year guidance to $3.4-3.8B, gross margin 31.5%. Product revenue $653M (+208%). Oracle Project Jupiter 2.45GW fuel cells. More than half of data center backlog from hyperscalers/neoclouds.\n\n\n- VST: Q1 2026 Revenue $5.64B (+43% YoY), Net Income $1.03B vs loss last year, EBITDA $1.49B vs expectations $1.44B\n- NEE: Q1 2026 GAAP net income $2.182B vs $833M last year, adjusted EPS $1.09 vs $0.99. Revenue $6.7B (-8% miss vs $7.29B expected). FPL added nearly 100,000 customers.\n\n**第二層 - 運算核心 (Compute Silicon)**\n- NVDA: $0.81 EPS\n\nNVIDIA reported $44.06B in revenue for Q1 2026, up 69% year-over-year, with a gross margin of 69.2%. AMD's Q1 revenue came in at $10.25B, a 38% increase, with Q2 guidance of $10.8-11.2B. Intel's Q1 saw $13.6B in revenue with data center and AI revenue jumping 22%, while non-GAAP gross margins expanded to around 41%, with Q2 guidance set at $13.8-14.8B. ARM Holdings reported Q1 revenue of $1.05B with royalty revenue of $585M, up 25% year-over-year.\n\nMoving down the stack, Micron reported a record Q1 with $23.9B in revenue and strong growth expectations, while Western Digital's Q2 showed $3.02-3.34B revenue (up 25-45% year-over-year) with non-GAAP EPS of $2.13-2.72. Seagate's fiscal Q3 saw $3.11B in revenue up 44% with non-GAAP EPS of $4.10, and they're projecting $3.45B for the next quarter. SK Hynix posted record Q1 results with revenue of 52.6 trillion KRW (approximately $37B) up 198% year-over-year, operating profit of 37.6 trillion won ($25.4B) up 405%, and an operating margin of 72%.\n\nNow looking at the networking layer, Broadcom reported Q1 revenue of $19.3B up 29% with AI revenue at $10.7B, while Marvell's AI business is now the majority of their data center segment. Arista Networks posted Q2 results with $2.71B in revenue up 35.1% and raised their outlook. For systems and cooling, Vertiv had strong momentum in Q2 with liquid cooling margins expanding, but Supermicro's Q3 showed a mixed picture—$10.2B in revenue up 123% year-over-year but missed expectations by over $2B, though their non-GAAP gross margin recovered to 10.1% from 6.4% sequentially. Eaton's Q1 revenue was $7.5B up 17%, and Foxconn is benefiting from AI server demand driving their multi-component growth.\n\nAt the models and MLOps layer, Microsoft's Q1 showed $82.9B revenue up 18% with Azure growing 39-40%, while Meta's Q1 had $55.02B in ad revenue up 33% and raised their capex guidance to $145B. Google's Q1 was particularly strong with $110B total revenue up 22% and Google Cloud hitting $20.03B up 63%, posting operating income of $6.6B versus $2.2B last year. ServiceNow's Q1 revenue was $3.67-3.77B up 19% year-over-year, and they've raised their AI-related revenue target from $1B to $1.5B.\n\nCrowdStrike's Q1 showed $1.10B in revenue up 20% year-over-year with ARR at $4.44B, though they guided for $1.14-1.15B in Q2 which came in slightly below expectations, resulting in some margin compression.\n\nNow I'm organizing all this earnings data into a structured seven-layer framework to give Jo a comprehensive analysis.\n","thinkingSignature":"79310a8f4f9d6a81a103e54a059de4938ebff702e14a96d0ff06e18925081da3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，數據收集完畢。以下是 Q2/Q1 2026 財報季報的完整七層蛋糕架構分析：\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Q2/Q1 2026 AI 七層蛋糕財報季報分析\n\n---\n\n### 🏛️ 第一層：能源與電力基建（Energy & Power）\n\n**BE（Bloom Energy）**\n- Q1 營收 $751M，暴增 **+130% YoY**，遠超預期 $540M\n- 產品營收 $653M（**+208% YoY**），占總營收 87%\n- 毛利率 31.5%，non-GAAP 獲利\n- 全年營收指引升至 **$3.4B–$3.8B**（舊上限已超過新下限）\n- Oracle Project Jupiter 將建 2.45GW 燃料電池微電網，取代天然氣渦輪+柴油\n- **重點**：超過一半的資料中心訂單來自 hyperscalers/neoclouds（除了 Oracle 以外的客戶）\n- 股價單日大漲 16%\n\n**VST（Vistra）**\n- Q1 營收 $5.64B（**+43% YoY**）\n- 淨利 $1.03B（去年同期虧損），EBITDA $1.49B > 預期 $1.44B\n- 2026 全年指引：EBITDA $6.8B–$7.6B，FCF $3.925B–$4.725B\n- **重點**：電力基建需求明確，但 Q1 營收小幅低於預期（$5.6B vs 預期 $5.7B），市場情緒偏謹慎\n\n**NEE（NextEra Energy）**\n- Q1 GAAP 淨利 $2.182B（去年同期 $833M），調整後 EPS $1.09 vs $0.99（**+10% YoY**）\n- 營收 $6.7B，**低於預期 $7.29B**（-8% 缺口）\n- FPL 新增近 10 萬客戶，計畫 2026-2032 年投資 $900 億–$1000 億\n- Energy Resources 新增 4GW 再生能源+儲能訂單（公司歷史新高）\n- **重點**：公用事業穩健，但營收不如預期；長線 8% EPS CAGR 成長看得清楚\n\n**CEG（Constellation Energy）**\n- 5月11日才公布財報（EPS $2.61 指引，搶先在前分析已提及）\n- 核能做為 24/7 基載電源，在電力緊缺時戰略價值最高\n\n**Ray 點評**：這層是 2026 年最被忽視的瓶頸。BE 和 VST 直接綁定 AI 資料中心用電，營收暴走式成長，但 NEE 這種大型公用事業因監管限制，爆發力相對溫吞。**能源是算力的天花板**——沒有電，GPU 再強也跑不動。\n\n---\n\n### 💻 第二層：運算核心（Compute Silicon）\n\n**INTC（Intel）**\n- Q1 營收 $13.6B（**+7% YoY**），非 GAAP 毛利率擴張至 ~41%\n- **Data Center & AI（DCAI）營收 +22%**，是本季最大亮點\n- Q2 指引 $13.8B–$14.8B，遠超華爾街預期\n- 18A 節點進入量產（HVM），美國政府入股 ~10%\n- 新 CEO Lip-Bu Tan 首個完整季度，股價單日大漲 15%\n- **重點**：INTC 真的在復甦了。DCAI 成長 22% 顯示 Xeon/AI 加速器開始被雲端客戶接受\n\n**ARM（ARM Holdings）**\n- Q1 營收 $1.05B（歷史第二高），Royalties $585M（**+25% YoY**）\n- Licensing $819M（+29% YoY），雖略低因前季基期高\n- Q2 指引 revenue $1.26B ±$50M（即 +20% YoY）\n- 長期目標：2031 年 AGI CPU 營收 $15B + IP 營收 $10B（→ EPS $9+）\n- **重點**：超過 2200 萬開發者在 ARM 架構上，超過全球 80% 的 base。資料中心滲透率上升，行動部門些微軟化\n\n**Ray 點評**：INTC 這次是真的觸底了，但投資人要記住——INTC 的 P/E 和預期已經不像破產股，股價大漲 15% 後性價比需要重新衡量。ARM 是「AI 時代的智財權收租股」，royalty 成長 25% 是相對穩定的收入流，但估值取決於市場願意給多少倍。\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 第三層：記憶體與儲存（Memory & Storage）\n\n**MU（Micron）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- 記錄 $23.9B 營收\n\n**WDC（Western Digital）**\n- Q2 FY2026：營收 $3.02B（**+25% YoY**），超預期 $2.93B\n- Non-GAAP EPS $2.13（另一數據顯示 $2.72 超共識）\n- HDD 出貨超過 350 萬台\n- **重點**：AI 儲存需求明確，但股價相對 MU 落後，WDC 性價比可能更高\n\n**STX（Seagate）**\n- Q3 FY2026：營收 $3.11B（**+44% YoY**），Non-GAAP EPS $4.10（> 預期 $3.50）\n- 毛利率創歷史新高，營業利益較去年同期翻倍，FCF 近 $1B\n- **HAMR Mozaic 4**：已量產出貨，兩大雲端廠商已完成認證，4TB+ 碟片產品\n- Q4 指引 $3.45B（遠超預期）\n- **重點**：STX 連續擊敗預期，44% YoY 增速比 WDC 更快，HAMR 技術領先\n\n**SK Hynix（000660.KS）**\n- Q1 營收 52.6 兆韓元（~**$37B +198% YoY**）\n- 營業利益 37.6 兆韓元（~**$25.4B +405% YoY**）\n- **Operating Margin 72%**（歷史新高）\n- DRAM 合約價漲幅 90-95%（QoQ），NAND 漲 55-60%（QoQ）\n- HBM 市佔率 **57%**，下半年預計推出 HBM4E 樣本\n- 宣布投資 19 兆韓元建設新韓國工廠\n- **重點**：SK Hynix 是這次記憶體超級週期的最大贏家，72% 邊際利潤是怪物級的數字\n\n**Ray 點評**：記憶體層是 Q2 最強的 layer。SNDK/MU 和 SK Hynix 的記憶體業務爆發，而 STX 和 WDC 的 HDD 業務也明顯受益於 AI 資料儲存需求。SK Hynix 的 72% OPM 是七層蛋糕中最頂層的毛利率表現，但估值也最貴。\n\n---\n\n### 🔗 第四層：高速互連與網路（Networking）\n\n**AVGO（Broadcom）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- Q1 營收 $19.3B（+29% YoY），AI 網路 $10.7B\n\n**MRVL（Marvell）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- AI 業務已成為資料中心多數營收\n\n**ANET（Arista Networks）**\n- Q2 營收 $2.71B（**+35.1% YoY**），**調升全年展望**\n- 雲端交換器需求持續暢旺，AI 工作負載帶動網路升級\n- **重點**：ANET 35% 增速是七層蛋糕網路層中最快的，而且數據中心交換器是一個相對穩定的 business，不容易被單一客戶砍單\n\n**Ray 點評**：MRVL 和 ANET 這季的股價表現說明市場對「網路是 AI 基建瓶頸」這件事越來越買單。ANET 的優勢是軟體定義網路（SDN）+ 白牌交換器，性價比高過純粹的 AI 晶片股。\n\n---\n\n### ⚙️ 第五層：系統、組裝與散熱（Systems & Cooling）\n\n**VRT（Vertiv）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- Q2 液冷系統毛利率持續擴張，動能股\n\n**SMCI（Super Micro Computer）**\n- Q3 FY2026：營收 $10.2B（**+123% YoY**），但**低於預期 $2.2B**\n- Non-GAAP 毛利率 **10.1%**（上季僅 6.4%，**大幅優於預期 6.75%**）——這是股價大漲 20% 的主因\n- 客戶現場合 Readiness 延遲（電力/網路），組件短缺\n- Q4 指引：EPS $0.65–$0.69（> 預期 $0.55），營收 $11B–$12.5B（> 預期 $11.07B）\n- **風險**：與共同創辦人 Wally Liaw 切斷關係（FBI 起訴），網路安全與誠信問題；集體訴訟；$75 億美元淨債務；現金轉換週期翻倍\n- **重點**：毛利率復甦是最大驚喜，但財務治理風險不容忽視\n\n**ETN（Eaton）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- Q1 營收 $7.5B（+17% YoY）\n\n**2317.TW（Foxconn/鴻海）**\n- 受惠 AI 伺服器需求，組裝業務持續成長\n- **重點**：鴻海是 NVDA HGX 系統組裝供應商，雖然毛利率低，但營收規模驚人\n\n**Ray 點評**：SMCI 這個名字充滿爭議——毛利率 10.1% 從 6.4% 快速回升是事實，但法律問題+債務問題讓它更像「深度價值/事件驅動」交易，而非穩定的 AI 基建股。VRT 的液冷紀律性更值得信賴。\n\n---\n\n### 🤖 第六層：基礎模型與平台（Models & MLOps）\n\n**MSFT（Microsoft）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- Q1 營收 $82.9B（+18% YoY），Azure +39-40%\n\n**META（Meta）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n- Q1 廣告營收 $55.02B（+33% YoY），Capex $145B\n\n**GOOGL（Alphabet/Google）**\n- Q1 總營收 $110B（**+22% YoY**，超越預期）\n- **Google Cloud $20.03B（+63% YoY）**，從 $2.2B → $6.6B 營業利益（**+181%**）\n- Cloud 佔整體營收 18%，是歷史最高比例\n- Alphabet 調升 2026 全年營收指引至 $180B–$190B（+$5B），並預計 2027 年進一步大幅增加 Capex\n- **重點**：Google Cloud 是這次財報季最大的驚喜。63% 成長顯示 TPUs 出租服務+企業 AI 採用正在規模化。CEO Sundar Pichai 明確表示 AI 是主要驅動力\n\n**Ray 點評**：GOOGL 這季證明了自己不是「落後的 AI 股」，而是真正的 AI 基礎設施玩家。Google Cloud 63% 增速和 MSFT Azure 40% 增速，兩者聯手告訴投資人：**雲端 AI 是 2026 年最確定性的成長故事**。\n\n---\n\n### 🕵️ 第七層：自主代理與應用變現（Agentic AI & Apps）\n\n**PLTR（Palantir）**（前一分析已涵蓋）\n\n**CRWD（CrowdStrike）**\n- Q1 FY2026：營收 $1.10B（**+20% YoY**），ARR $4.44B（+22% YoY）\n- Subscription gross margin **80%**，AI 平台效率明顯\n- GAAP 虧損 $110.2M（去年同期 $42.8M 獲利），因上次軟體更新事故導致成本墊高\n- Q2 指引：營收 $1.14B–$1.15B（略低於預期 $1.16B），Non-GAAP EPS $0.82–$0.84\n- Falcon Flex 模式已有 $32 億封閉交易價值（+31% QoQ，+6 倍 YoY）\n- **重點**：營收 20% 成長但毛利率 80%，顯示軟體 AI 平台槓桿極高，但營收指引輕微低於預期讓市場觀望\n\n**NOW（ServiceNow）**\n- Q1 營收 $3.77B（**+19% YoY**）\n- **AI 相關營收目標：從 $1B 升至 $1.5B**（加速中）\n- 完整年度訂閱營收指引：$15.755B（約 +21% YoY）\n- AI 專家與 Google Gemini AI agents 合作\n- **重點**：ServiceNow 是企業 AI Agent 的重要平台，Q1 顯示 AI 變現比預期更快，目標上調 50% 是重要信號\n\n**Ray 點評**：CRWD 和 NOW 都是 SaaS/AI 安全和自動化和 Agentic AI 的領導者，但估值都已反映高度成長。CRWD 的 80% 毛利率令人印象深刻，但營收增速放緩至 20% 是需要注意的信號。NOW 的 AI 營收目標大幅上調，顯示企業 AI Agent 採用正在加速。\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 總結：七層蛋糕 Q2 季報全景\n\n| 層次 | 股票 | Q2/Q1 重點 | 評價 |\n|------|------|-----------|------|\n| 🏛️ 能源 | BE/VST/CEG/NEE | BE +130% 最猛，VST 穩健，NEE 營收低預期 | 電力瓶頸真實存在，但股價已部分反映 |\n| 💻 運算 | INTC/AMD/ARM/NVDA | INTC +22% DCAI 觸底反彈，ARM royalty +25% | NVDA 仍是主導者；INTC 需觀察持續性 |\n| 🧠 記憶體 | MU/WDC/STX/SK Hynix | SK Hynix OPM 72% 怪獸級，STX +44% 增速加快 | 記憶體超級週期仍在進行 |\n| 🔗 網路 | AVGO/MRVL/ANET | ANET +35.1% 調升展望，MRVL AI 多數營收 | 網路瓶頸被低估 |\n| ⚙️ 系統 | VRT/SMCI/ETN/2317 | SMCI 毛利率復甦但治理風險高；VRT 動能持續 | VRT 紀律性最佳；SMCI 需謹慎 |\n| 🤖 模型 | MSFT/META/GOOGL | GOOGL Cloud +63% 季報最大驚喜 | 雲端 AI 確定性最強 |\n| 🕵️ Agent | PLTR/CRWD/NOW | NOW AI 營收目標升至 $1.5B；CRWD 毛利 80% | Agentic AI 變現正在加速 |\n\n**Ray 的核心觀點**：這次財報季最重要的結論是——**能源是算力上限，雲端是 AI 變現入口**。記憶體（SK Hynix/STX）和雲端 AI（GOOGL/MSFT）是我認為 Q2 最應該持續關注的兩層工廠。SMCI 需要謹慎，INTC 底部確認但性價比需重新衡量。\n\n📈"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6711,"output":4665,"cacheRead":37408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48784,"cost":{"input":0.0020133,"output":0.005598,"cacheRead":0.0022444799999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00985578}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778387648397,"responseId":"064f3dc233660cfb0e30359d6cbb2d73"}}
