{"type":"message","id":"5b6c29b3","parentId":"fa03b31e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:20:58.077Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_brb9kch6q11f_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Marvell MRVL annual revenue FY2026 guidance AI data center\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1551,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d0a4051504d409d0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell posts record FY26 revenue and AI-driven growth | MRVL 8-K Filing\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d0a4051504d409d0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/MRVL/8-k-marvell-technology-inc-reports-material-event-47fac4664202.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5bd736dc2421e201\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n**Marvell Technology, Inc.** reported very strong results for the fourth quarter and fiscal year ended January 31, 2026, driven by demand for AI and data center products. Q4 net revenue was **$2.219 billion**, up **22% year-on-year**, with GAAP diluted EPS of **$0.46** and non-GAAP diluted EPS of **$0.80**. GAAP net income was **$2.670 billion** (GAAP diluted EPS **$3.07**), compared with a prior-year GAAP net loss, while non-GAAP net income was **$2.466 billion** (non-GAAP diluted EPS **$2.84**), up **81% year-over-year** per management. Management expects year-over-year revenue growth to accelerate each quarter in fiscal 2027 and has issued Q1 fiscal 2027 guidance for net revenue of **$2.400 billion ±5%** with non-GAAP diluted EPS of **$0.79 ±$0.05**, including expected contributions from the Celestial AI and XConn Technologies acquisitions. * **Record fiscal 2026 performance**: Net revenue reached $8.195 billion, up 42% year-over-year, with non-GAAP diluted EPS of $2.84 described as increasing 81%, marking a strong turnaround from the prior-year GAAP net loss.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5bd736dc2421e201\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9604838\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"334d582df1cdad3d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell projects strong fiscal 2028 revenue on AI-driven data center boom, shares jump\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"334d582df1cdad3d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reuters.com/technology/marvell-forecasts-first-quarter-revenue-above-estimates-2026-03-05/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"579a6430b88b8b77\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n*   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). ## [Browse World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). ## [Browse Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Take Five](https://www.reuters.com/business/take-five/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). ## [Browse Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). March 5 (Reuters) - Marvell Technology [(MRVL.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/MRVL.O) forecast fiscal 2028 revenue above Wall Street ‌estimates on Thursday, signaling robust demand for custom chips and interconnect solutions used in artificial intelligence data centers, sending its shares surging 15% in extended trading. Marvell and rival Broadcom [(AVGO.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/AVGO.O) help cloud-computing companies design custom chips tailored to their data-center workloads, a fast-growing business as hyperscalers seek alternatives to Nvidia's [(NVDA.O), opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/markets/companies/NVDA.O) general-purpose AI processors. Broadcom on Wednesday said it expected over [$100 billion in AI chip sales next year](https://www.reuters.com/technology/broadcom-forecasts-second-quarter-revenue-above-estimates-2026-03-04/), signaling rapid share gains in a market dominated by Nvidia, which last month reported [better-than-expected results](https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/nvidia-forecasts-first-quarter-sales-above-estimates-2026-02-25/) for the January quarter. Our Standards: [The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles., opens new tab](https://www.thomsonreuters.com/en/about-us/trust-principles.html). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [Home](https://www.reuters.com/). *   [World](https://www.reuters.com/world/). *   [Business](https://www.reuters.com/business/). *   [Markets](https://www.reuters.com/markets/). *   [Media Center, opens new tab](https://www.reuters.com/media-center/). *   [](https://www.facebook.com/Reuters). *   [](https://www.instagram.com/Reuters).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"579a6430b88b8b77\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8742601\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f8a69df8b0a61de4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPerplexity\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f8a69df8b0a61de4\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.perplexity.ai/finance/MRVL/earnings\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc72caafd7e90add\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# Marvell Technology, Inc. Overview Financials Earnings Holders Historical Data Analysis. (NASDAQ: MRVL) is a leading fabless semiconductor company headquartered in Wilmington, Delaware, that designs, develops, and sells a broad portfolio of analog, mixed-signal, digital signal processing, and embedded integrated circuits primarily serving data infrastructure markets. Murphy since 2016, the company serves five key end markets — data center, enterprise networking, carrier infrastructure, consumer, and automotive/industrial — with its data center segment emerging as the dominant growth driver, reporting a 76.5% year-over-year revenue increase to $1.44 billion in Q1 fiscal 2026 fueled by robust demand for custom AI accelerators (XPUs), optical interconnect solutions, and advanced packaging technologies. With fiscal year 2025 net revenues of approximately $5.8 billion and a market capitalization exceeding $136 billion, Marvell has firmly established itself as a critical enabler of AI-driven data infrastructure, competing against industry giants including Broadcom, NVIDIA, and Qualcomm. Reported revenue and EPS data from Earnings powered by Fiscal.ai. By clicking \\\"Accept All Cookies\\\" or selecting \\\"Necessary Cookies\\\", you agree to our privacy policy.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"bc72caafd7e90add\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8708723\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b48adf8b73050216\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell: Rating Upgrade On Data Center Boom - Seeking Alpha\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b48adf8b73050216\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4890006-marvell-rating-upgrade-on-data-center-boom\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7a48bbf4ed01f83c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell's revenue disclosed by management is only a mere $300 million here in FY2026, but its strong guidance to double in FY2027 indicates\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7a48bbf4ed01f83c\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8536326\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d17159bdf147d550\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMarvell Technology Q4 FY 2026 Earnings Raise Growth Outlook - Futurum\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d17159bdf147d550\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://futurumgroup.com/insights/marvell-technology-q4-fy-2026-earnings-raise-data-center-growth-outlook/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fe96162a1748752b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGet organization-wide instant access to market sizing and decision-maker data in a self-serve subscription model with analyst support. Turn your message into motion with analyst-hosted video, live events, digital media, and content strategies. # Futurum Research 2026: Key Issues and Predictions. Marvell Technology’s Q4 FY 2026 results and commentary point to a faster data center expansion cycle, with higher visibility from accelerating bookings and expanding attach across AI infrastructure. “We expect YoY revenue growth to accelerate each quarter in fiscal 2027, driven by continued strength in our data center business, with bookings continuing to grow at a record pace.”. **Analyst Take:** Marvell’s Q4 FY 2026 update reflects a company leaning into higher confidence around AI infrastructure demand, with management tying the raised outlook to accelerating bookings and expanding content across multiple data center product lines. Due to the fast pace of content creation and the continuous evolution of data and information, The Futurum Group and its analysts strive to ensure the accuracy and factual integrity of the information presented.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fe96162a1748752b\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8215175\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["query","provider","count","tookMs","externalContent","results"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778401258076}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8d71d80","parentId":"5b6c29b3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:21:08.593Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the key data for MRVL:\n- Market cap: ~$148.77B (as of May 2026)\n- FY2026 revenue: $8.195B (up 42% YoY)\n- P/E: 55.42\n- Q1 FY2027 guidance: $2.40B ±5%\n- Non-GAAP EPS FY2026: $2.84\n\nLet me now get the comparable data for other AI stocks to give Jo a proper comparison.\n","thinkingSignature":"d0126956dfc30cddd57e3cab302eff6b209acde74d5c99b3f9fbe0b67a52a67d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_duf303if9r8f_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"NVDA AMD AVGO ANET market cap PE ratio revenue comparison 2026"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3553,"output":155,"cacheRead":48800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52508,"cost":{"input":0.0010659,"output":0.000186,"cacheRead":0.0029279999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004179899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778401258077,"responseId":"064f72ea61fce828bbd85c2d520dd8b4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c967b182","parentId":"b8d71d80","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:21:10.657Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_duf303if9r8f_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"NVDA AMD AVGO ANET market cap PE ratio revenue comparison 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1602,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0478003e33895359\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNvidia vs Broadcom: Which AI Stock Will Make You More Money - AOL\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0478003e33895359\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.aol.com/articles/nvidia-vs-broadcom-ai-stock-154211894.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"040820582ba7869f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNvidia posted Q4 revenue of $68.13 billion, up 73.2% year-over-year, while Broadcom delivered Q1 FY2026 revenue of $19.31 billion, up 29.5% year-over-year. Nvidia (NVDA) posted Q4 revenue of $68.13B, up 73.2% year-over-year, with Data Center revenue reaching $62.31B and networking revenue surging 263% year-over-year to $10.98B. Broadcom (AVGO) delivered Q1 FY2026 revenue of $19.31B, up 29.5% year-over-year, with AI chip revenue hitting $8.40B, up 106% year-over-year, and management guiding Q2 AI semiconductor revenue to $10.7B. Nvidia dominates as a broad platform supplier of GPUs and NVLink fabric across cloud providers and enterprises, while Broadcom pursues custom AI accelerators and Ethernet AI switches tailored for hyperscaler workflows, creating stickier relationships but higher customer concentration risk. Data Center revenue reached $62.31 billion, up 75% year-over-year, with networking revenue alone surging 263% year-over-year to $10.98 billion as NVLink fabric scaled across GB200 and GB300 systems.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"040820582ba7869f\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.8025714\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e20b7224deb597c2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow Does Broadcom Stock Stack Up Against Its Peers? - Forbes\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e20b7224deb597c2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/greatspeculations/2026/02/05/how-does-broadcom-stock-stack-up-against-its-peers/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ffe9fa4042f0cca9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAVGO's 39.7% stock increase and a PE ratio of 63.0 mirror optimism for AI infrastructure; nonetheless, NVDA/AMD have recorded stronger returns\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ffe9fa4042f0cca9\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.7892503\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e6308b1c5331d31f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNVIDIA vs. Broadcom: The Smarter AI Stock to Buy for March 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e6308b1c5331d31f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nvidia-vs-broadcom-smarter-ai-200000819.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2ec39e2fc735c47a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPer the price/earnings ratio, NVDA trades at 25.14 forward earnings compared with AVGO's forward earnings multiple of 31.38.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2ec39e2fc735c47a\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.78074646\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"81206d2898096bc5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAVGO vs NVDA: Yield, P/E & Performance (2026) | AllInvestView\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"81206d2898096bc5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.allinvestview.com/compare/AVGO-vs-NVDA/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f536991bd8d67e19\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBroadcom Inc. (AVGO) vs NVIDIA Corporation (NVDA) in 2026 — live price, dividend yield, P/E ratio, beta, growth, and analyst targets compared side by side.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f536991bd8d67e19\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.70067\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c29f1ad9104d8009\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNVDA vs AVGO: Performance Charts & Full Comparison | PortfoliosLab\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c29f1ad9104d8009\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://portfolioslab.com/tools/stock-comparison/NVDA/AVGO\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"beda86d501a46c10\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n**NVDA** (NVIDIA Corporation) is a stock, while **AVGO** (Broadcom Inc.) is a stock. Over the past 10 years, NVDA returned 72.22%/yr vs 43.80%/yr for AVGO. In the year-to-date period, NVDA achieves a 6.43% return, which is significantly lower than AVGO's 20.59% return. Over the past 10 years, NVDA has outperformed AVGO with an annualized return of 72.22%, while AVGO has yielded a comparatively lower 43.80% annualized return. The correlation between NVDA and AVGO is **0.54**, which is moderate. | Correlation (1Y) Calculated over the trailing 1-year period | 0.54 |. This table presents a comparison of risk-adjusted performance metrics for NVIDIA Corporation (NVDA) and Broadcom Inc. Risk-adjusted metrics are performance indicators that assess an investment's returns in relation to its risk, enabling a more accurate comparison of different investment options. The current NVDA Sharpe Ratio is **2.19**, which is comparable to the AVGO Sharpe Ratio of **2.52**. | Sharpe Ratio (1Y)Calculated over the trailing 1-year period | 2.19 | 2.52 | -0.33 |.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"beda86d501a46c10\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.64182705\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"NVDA AMD AVGO ANET market cap PE ratio revenue comparison 2026","provider":