1\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.999944\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e85d21e58bd8f52b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArista Networks (ANET) - P/E ratio\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e85d21e58bd8f52b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://companiesmarketcap.com/arista-networks/pe-ratio/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"05ead6a2822a2f77\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# P/E ratio for Arista Networks (ANET). At the end of 2024 the company had a P/E ratio of **48.6**. ## P/E ratio history for Arista Networks from 2014 to 2025. ### P/E ratio for similar companies or competitors. | Company | P/E ratio | P/E ratio differencediff. A **low but positive P/E ratio** stands for a company that is generating high earnings compared to its current valuation and might be undervalued. A company with a **high negative (near 0) P/E ratio** stands for a company that is generating heavy losses compared to its current valuation. Companies with a P/E ratio over 30 or a negative one are generaly seen as \\\"growth stocks\\\" meaning that investors typically expect the company to grow or to become profitable in the future. Companies with a positive P/E ratio bellow 10 are generally seen as \\\"value stocks\\\" meaning that the company is already very profitable and unlikely to strong growth in the future.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"05ead6a2822a2f77\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.999892\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4502822f76125aef\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nArista Networks (ANET) PE Ratio - Current & Historical Data (May ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4502822f76125aef\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.financecharts.com/stocks/ANET/value/pe-ratio\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7c29811c6d33eb6d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe pe ratio for Arista Networks (ANET) stock is 48.55 as of Friday, May 08 2026. It's improved by -1.48% from its 12-month average of 49.28.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7c29811c6d33eb6d\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9998746\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d64861abb6c4bec9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nANET 2026 Earnings & EPS History - Quarterly & Annual Growth Reports\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d64861abb6c4bec9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://fullratio.com/stocks/nyse-anet/earnings\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c6281aa396ebd3a4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n# ANET Arista Networks Earnings and EPS analysis. Relative Growth:  Rel. Growth:  98. Arista Networks's EPS for 2025 amounted to $2.79, marking an increase from $2.27 in 2024. During the quarterly period ending on Dec 31, 2025, ANET's EPS stood at $0.76. Historical annual and quarterly earnings per share (EPS) data for Arista Networks. Arista Networks had an annual EPS of $2.79, indicating an increase of 22.9% from $2.27 in 2024. The quarterly per-share earnings for the period ending Dec 31, 2025, was $0.76, indicating a 18.8% increase from the same quarter last year. Arista Networks's annual EPS in 2024 stood at $2.27, a 34.3% increase year-over-year. ## ANET EPS growth. During the last 12 months, Arista Networks has seen an EPS growth of 18.8% (YoY, quarterly). Throughout the last three years, the company had an average EPS growth of 36.4% per year. During the last 5 years, the company had an average EPS growth rate of 39.9%.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c6281aa396ebd3a4\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9998118\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a7720f4659e25e28\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nANET Stock Price | Arista Networks P/E, Revenue, EPS, & Forecasts\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a7720f4659e25e28\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://wealthyhood.com/en/stocks/anet.nyse/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6f51334c7e760d52\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n### Arista Networks• ANET. ##### About Arista Networks. Arista Networks, Inc. engages in the development, marketing, and sale of data-driven, client to cloud networking solutions for AI, data center, campus, and routing environments in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and the Asia-Pacific. Its cloud networking solutions consist of Extensible Operating System (EOS), a publish-subscribe state-sharing networking operating system offered in combination with a set of network applications. The company offers data center, cloud and AI networking, cognitive adjacencies, and cognitive network software and services. Arista Networks, Inc. was formerly known as Arastra, Inc. and changed its name to Arista Networks, Inc. in October 2008. The company was incorporated in 2004 and is headquartered in Santa Clara, California. ###### P/E ratio. ###### Forward P/E ratio. ###### Dividend per share. ###### Forward dividend per share. What is the 200-day moving average of Arista Networks? What is the market cap of Arista Networks? What is the P/E of Arista Networks?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6f51334c7e760d52\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99955577\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"ANET Arista Networks market cap PE ratio revenue 2026","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1450,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8413863d59fb73ec\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nARISTA NETWORKS PE Ratio: 62.54 — 55% Above Median\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8413863d59fb73ec\">>>","url":"https://www.gurufocus.com/term/pe-ratio/ANET","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c8639cee44e54271\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# ARISTA NETWORKS PE Ratio: 62.54 — 55% Above Median. *   Peter Lynch Growth w Lower Valuation 1 New. *   Peter Lynch S&L Traded Below Book 20 New. *   Predictable Growth Companies 4 New. *   S&P 500 Grid 20 New. *   Historical Low P/S List 3 New. *   Top 25 Historical Low P/S. *   GF Value for S&P 500 Index. *   Operating Cash Flow per Share. *   Price-to-Operating-Cash-Flow. The PE Ratio, or Price-to-Earnings ratio, or P/E Ratio, is a financial ratio used to compare a company's market price to its Earnings per Share (Diluted). Arista Networks's Earnings per Share (Diluted) for the **trailing twelve months (TTM)** ended in **Dec. 2025** was **$2.76**. Therefore, Arista Networks's PE Ratio for **today** is **62.54**. Similar to the PE Ratio without NRI or PS Ratio or Price-to-Operating-Cash-Flow or Price-to-Free-Cash-Flow, the PE Ratio measures the valuation based on the earning power of the company. P/E ratio is the ratio of share price to a company's earnings per share.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c8639cee44e54271\">>>","score":0.999944},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e85d21e58bd8f52b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nArista Networks (ANET) - P/E ratio\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e85d21e58bd8f52b\">>>","url":"https://companiesmarketcap.com/arista-networks/pe-ratio/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"05ead6a2822a2f77\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# P/E ratio for Arista Networks (ANET). At the end of 2024 the company had a P/E ratio of **48.6**. ## P/E ratio history for Arista Networks from 2014 to 2025. ### P/E ratio for similar companies or competitors. | Company | P/E ratio | P/E ratio differencediff. A **low but positive P/E ratio** stands for a company that is generating high earnings compared to its current valuation and might be undervalued. A company with a **high negative (near 0) P/E ratio** stands for a company that is generating heavy losses compared to its current valuation. Companies with a P/E ratio over 30 or a negative one are generaly seen as \"growth stocks\" meaning that investors typically expect the company to grow or to become profitable in the future. Companies with a positive P/E ratio bellow 10 are generally seen as \"value stocks\" meaning that the company is already very profitable and unlikely to strong growth in the future.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"05ead6a2822a2f77\">>>","score":0.999892},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4502822f76125aef\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nArista Networks (ANET) PE Ratio - Current & Historical Data (May ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4502822f76125aef\">>>","url":"https://www.financecharts.com/stocks/ANET/value/pe-ratio","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7c29811c6d33eb6d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe pe ratio for Arista Networks (ANET) stock is 48.55 as of Friday, May 08 2026. It's improved by -1.48% from its 12-month average of 49.28.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7c29811c6d33eb6d\">>>","score":0.9998746},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d64861abb6c4bec9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nANET 2026 Earnings & EPS History - Quarterly & Annual Growth Reports\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d64861abb6c4bec9\">>>","url":"https://fullratio.com/stocks/nyse-anet/earnings","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c6281aa396ebd3a4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n# ANET Arista Networks Earnings and EPS analysis. Relative Growth:  Rel. Growth:  98. Arista Networks's EPS for 2025 amounted to $2.79, marking an increase from $2.27 in 2024. During the quarterly period ending on Dec 31, 2025, ANET's EPS stood at $0.76. Historical annual and quarterly earnings per share (EPS) data for Arista Networks. Arista Networks had an annual EPS of $2.79, indicating an increase of 22.9% from $2.27 in 2024. The quarterly per-share earnings for the period ending Dec 31, 2025, was $0.76, indicating a 18.8% increase from the same quarter last year. Arista Networks's annual EPS in 2024 stood at $2.27, a 34.3% increase year-over-year. ## ANET EPS growt