{"type":"message","id":"4d3716a3","parentId":"2a919703","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:22:07.004Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compile the comparison. Let me also search for ANET's market cap since I didn't find it yet.\n\nFrom the data:\n- NVDA: Market cap ~$5.05T-$5.23T (May 2026), PE ~25 (forward), TTM PE ~55-65 range\n- AVGO: Market cap ~$2.03T-$2.04T, PE ~63 (trailing), ~38 (forward), Revenue $19.3B\n- MRVL: Market cap ~$148B, PE ~55 (TTM), Revenue FY2026 $8.2B (+42% YoY)\n\n\n- AMD: Market cap ~$579B, PE ~65 (TTM), Revenue Q1 $10.25B (+38% YoY)\n- ANET: Market cap roughly $95B based on a $48 PE ratio against $2.79 annual EPS\n\nFor valuation multiples, AVGO trades at a notably higher trailing PE of 63-83 compared to NVDA's 25, suggesting the market is pricing in significant future growth expectations for Broadcom.\n\nLooking at PS ratios, NVDA commands a premium at 35x next twelve months revenue versus AVGO at 30x, while ANET sits at a more reasonable 16-17x and MRVL at 18x. MRVL's fiscal 2026 revenue of $8.2B with 42% year-over-year growth gives it a compelling position as the fastest grower among these network players, trailing only NVDA and AMD in absolute scale but ahead of ANET's $10.8B run rate.","thinkingSignature":"612a83fb235aa92907216c095d769e12ffdaa61024a821c3f236972d38112b44"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ph73bu8ic84h_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":3,"query":"ANET Arista Networks market cap total value 2026"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2369,"output":385,"cacheRead":59680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62434,"cost":{"input":0.0007107,"output":0.00046199999999999995,"cacheRead":0.0035808,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0047535}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778401299857,"responseId":"064f7316a2b97d8d557727c7a791b3e0"}}
